text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
‘to be a man’: a portrait series challenging the concept of toxic masculinity. ~denom. nepal.~
“it's ok for me to show my emotions and cry. there is nothing wrong with showing your soft side. we all are humans and these feelings are completely normal. it is not wrong for men to cry at all! in fact, i would say it is vital for men to cry, to let their emotions out and share their feelings with others. there are cultures where men are not supposed to cry or at least hide their weaknesses, it's better if they seem more controlled and emotionally numb. people think if we cry we’re linked to weakness since we can't take control over our emotions. we hear phrases like, “don’t be a pussy”, “stop being a girl” a lot. if we keep hearing phrases like these, what do boys all around the world think about being boys today? whom will they look up to, and how will they navigate the transition from being boys to becoming men?” check out the full project on www.jessicaamity.com
.
.
.
#thebestmencanbe #metoo #heforshe #mentalhealthawareness #mentalhealth #menshealth #toxicmasculinity #masculinity #instagood #mentalhealthsupport #mentalhealthadvocate

text:
#walkwithwambui 
most of you have been asking why i spoke up and put my story out here

well i was in a dark place....depression took the best part of me, i hated myself to the point of almost commiting suicide on several occasions i even developed ulcers😪😪 it was so hard for me to paint a perfect picture of me to the outside world while i was really drowning on the inside. hide my scars was soo hard, painful and exhausting...... but during all this period my innerself would talk to me....asking whether i would want my daughter or son to go through what i was going through... and i would tell myself no! because sexual assault/violence leaves more than just physical wounds and depression is hell😓 and it would really hurt me to see our daughters and sons go through this hell and maybe i could have prevented it....
..... so i got tired of just sitting and waiting for change to occur while i could bring the change
 i am doing this for myself and others out here who are facing this and to secure a great and better  future for our kids😊

#hearmetoo 
#metoo 
#zerosexualassault 
#mentalhealthmatters
#thefutureisinourhands

ogni parola di un soggetto tossico è studiata per avere una vostra reazione, ogni incontro è studiato a tavolino e non c’è nulla di improvvisato, ogni argomento che “casualmente” emerge nella conversazione è scelto per farvi pensare, per crearvi ansia, dolore, nostalgia,  a seconda delle intenzioni del momento. non è possibile essere mai se stessi, sarete costretti a difendervi costantemente da accuse, offese, illazioni, sospetti. arriverete a temere le reazioni, i momenti negativi, imparerete ad anticiparli. vivrete nell’ansia, nel timore costante di essere sostituiti da quell’amica così cara, da quell’amico così simpatico e avrete costanti emicranie, dolori allo stomaco, conati di vomito, voglia di piangere, tristezza profonda. ancora dite che non riuscite a lasciarli? ancora lo chiamate amore? davvero riuscite ancora a ricordare i bei momenti iniziali e credere fossero veri?

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
and so it begins. 
i used to love going to walks on my own. to clear my head and get ideas. 
but now i am too afraid. to many times have groups of grown men in cars trailed me and tried to pull me in.

and that is not ok. this is not ok. we can't live in fear forever.
especially knowing that the justice system is also slow and the conviction rate so low.

the amount of times i could have reported someone for sexual assault or rape is just beyond a joke. 
and yet i was always scared of what they would do to me, if the justice system failed 'because they have dependants, because they have a career.' i was scared i would end up dead.

not going out running alone does not solve sexual assault and rape. it's everywhere. 
it's even in your home at the hands of your partner.

telling women to not be free is not the answer. there being a serious and absolute penalty for this kind of behaviour is.

#enoughisenough #metoo #womenempoweringwomen

text:
sex·u·al ha·rass·ment

noun: sexual harassment
behavior characterized by the making of unwelcome and inappropriate sexual remarks or physical advances in a workplace or other professional or social situation.

sexual harassment isn’t just affecting hollywood or corporate america, it’s also affecting our federal government - federal employees who have remained silent.

it’s time to “shutdown” sexual harassment in the federal government. victims have been wrongfully terminated from their jobs as a result of reporting, making it difficult or even impossible to be re-employed by the federal system.

text: rape culture and the ideas around what constitutes rape have been warped for centuries. i think the singular most important thing to know is-if you did not consent to a sexual act that took place is it rape. regardless of whether you were okay with it prior and changed your mind, no means no. rape has many forms and it's important to know if you were sexually violated against your will no matter the circumstances you do not need to feel ashamed, less than whole or hide away because of what you are going through. lastly rape happens to men too, so be aware and stay alert. #rape #rapeculture #rapesurvivor #rapeisrape #sexeducation #nomeansno #metoo #thursdaythoughts

text:
♡
it was 24°
at 3:39 in the afternoon
as my head swam
in doubt filled swells
waiting for the ringing
to respond ~
my gaze fixed
past the winter film that gathered on the glass doors 
down the road 
that sweep back up
through the empty canopies
backed by heavy clouds
to the glaring sod landscape
decorated with the overpriced and underused 
ford pickup truck and jeep
that held more than just my attention 
for 
too long
when the ringing
finally 
respoded
"you survived."
.
.
.

text_retweet:
#repost @muslimahnewsid (@get_repost)
・・・
/ perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks /
.
pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.
.
pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya atau gerakan #metoo yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.
.
pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, “pertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai ‘amanah’ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa ‘kontrol seksual’ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.”
.
kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah.
.
“menjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,” ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019).
.
.
——

.

seguint el fil que ha encetat @elenacrespi81 volia denunciar públicament que des de que tenc els meus perfils professionals he rebut multitud de sol·licituds únicament encaminades a fer-me arribar propostes sexuals, fotografies explícites o excuses professionals que han acabat en assetjament. 
no ha estat una vegada, ni dues ni vint.. és constant, i sempre per part d'homes.

pensen que ser psicològa i sexòloga vol dir treballadora sexual? 
podria ser, però no ho crec. pens que aprofiten aquestes xarxes i perfils anònims per fer allò que realment voldrien, sense repressió però sempre amb la frase final preparada de: 'pensava era la teva feina', 'hauries de ser més oberta', 'si et dediques això deus estar acostumada'... i sí hi estic, per desgràcia, però no forma part de la meva feina. 
i des de fa poc, però fermament, he decidit que ja no hi ha resposta, no hi ha reflexió, no hi ha joc ni culpa de deure professional. 
bloqueig. denúncia. final. 
#assetjamentsexual #sexologaorgullosa 
#denuncia

text:
footage of nigel farage swigging a pint and thanking steve bannon and breitbart for the brexit result was deleted from a breitbart youtube channel, following the data scandal surrounding cambridge analytica.
.
- well done bannon, well done breitbart, the ex-ukip leader announces in the short clip. - you helped with this. hugely.

farage’s nod to steve bannon certainly hasn’t aged well in the context of the recent storm around cambridge analytica’s influence over the eu referendum.

it was revealed that data from 50 million facebook profiles were looked at against the electoral register, and then used to build an algorithm which analyses people’s personality traits in relation to their voting behaviour.

this data could then be used to find potential swing voters and create messages tailored to influence them politically.

the firm’s vice president at the time was steve bannon, who was also head of the right-wing website breitbart and was running donald trump’s campaign to become us president.

anna o'donohue
inews

text:
the symbol of the rising phoenix, means so much to me. it symbolizes my rise from the hell fire i endured in my former life. all the physical, mental and sexual abuses, the poverty, moving every year for my whole life. therefore having no roots. the bullying i endured growing up, always the angry loner and outcast. the trips to the children's psychiatric hospital. all the self hate. all the thoughts and attempts of suicide. all the self sabotage and destruction. all the self inflicted torment. the devastating disease that is addiction and alcoholism. by the grace of god out of these ashes of my former life i have risen, with all the intense fury and rage of the rising sun. for i am the male version of the rising phoenix. i am the warrior of god. i was born in the intense heat and pressure of a living hell. i will not crack, i will take no quarter and none shall be given. god has given me a mission. to save the abused, neglected, bullied and poverty stricken children of this world. i will gladly trade my life for just one child. i pledge my sword and my life to this cause. i pray to die a martyr's death, for there is no greater honor than to die for and in the path of god. know my resolve. know my  commitment. know i want to die a martyr's death. know i am warrior, the warrior of god. know my belief and my faith in god is unshakeable. know i will not and can not be defeated, unless god wills it, for god is with me. may god have no mercy on those that prey on children. may they all burn in hell fire forever....
may god bless you all 🍀🍀🍀❤️❤️❤️🙏🙏🙏🐺

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaign’s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there “could have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheating”. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesday’s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

text:
hoy cumple 18 años ahed tamimi, un auténtico símbolo de la resistencia palestina.
aprovecho su día para homenajearla compartiendo estos dos dibujos que formaron parte de mis dos últimas exposiciones y contando muy resumidamente la historia de la ocupación de su pueblo.

en 1945 finaliza la ii guerra mundial y el mundo se entera cabalmente del holocausto perpetrado por los nazis. algo que refuerza la presión de los judíos sionistas por emigrar a palestina, reclamando como propia una tierra en la que ya vivían 1.380.000 palestinos.

las presiones del sionismo, en gran parte de forma armada mediante grupos paramilitares, logra echar de palestina a los británicos y obliga a las naciones unidas a involucrarse, dando lugar a una de las resoluciones más injustas y desacertadas de la historia. 
el 29 de noviembre de 1947 se determina la partición de palestina en 2 estados y de forma sorprendente se entrega el 56% del territorio a un pueblo judío (israel) que por aquel entonces solo suponía el 33% de la población total. 
nada más crearse el estado de israel, el sionismo desata su actividad terrorista. por ejemplo en la masacre de deir yassin, en la que fueron asesinados 250 palestinos y con la cual se envió un mensaje a la población en el que se dejó claro que o abandonaban el territorio o correrían la misma suerte.

desde entonces, ia política invasiva de israel se ha hecho con la mayor parte del terreno y acumula en su curriculum miles de asesinatos de civiles, la creación de guetos, la construcción del muro de la vergüenza, demolición de miles de hogares, detenciones arbitrarias, torturas, bloqueo militar y una continua violación de los derechos humanos de la cual el resto del mundo se desentiende vergonzosamente día tras día.
.
.
.

text:
rose mcgowan - napewno kojarzycie tę aktorkę z serialu czarodziejki, zagrała tam odnalezioną po latach siostrę halliwell - paige matthews. 
w swojej książce dzieli się z czytelnikami swoim życiem, które nie było usłane różami. od trudnego dzieciństwa spędzonego w sekcie poprzez bezdomność do wyzwolenia jako kobieta. 
ta książka to opis niezwykle silnej kobiety, która niejednokrotnie upadała. to także manifest i walka o równość i godność kobiet. rose ukazuje nam jak traktowane są kobiety w hollywood: jak przedmioty do seksualnej przyjemności mężczyzn. autorka nie kryje tego, że wielokrotnie była molestowana i zgwałcona - przez znanego producenta. gdy zaczęła głośno mówić nie dla poniżania kobiet- nie dostawała ról. była jedną z pierwszych, która publicznie oskarżyła harveya weinsteina o gwałt zapoczątkowując głośną na cały świat akcje #metoo

text:
freida pinto talks about the future for hollywood post-#metoo
#
by the time freida pinto and i collect our lemon ginger teas from a coffee shop in the leafy hancock park neighbourhood of los angeles, the table we had been eyeing outside has been taken. pinto turns to me and says, “let’s go,” then dashes across larchmont boulevard and slips into a nearby cafe, hoping no one will notice that we byo’d. “i have breakfast here every other morning. it should be fine,” she says with that megawatt smile. it’s hard to imagine anyone ever says no to her. “but they might just kick us out who knows. i never take anything for granted anymore.” after her breakout role in danny boyle’s multi-oscar-winning slumdog millionaire, pinto has quietly scored part after part, working with the most celebrated directors in cinema today (julian schnabel, michael winterbottom and terrance malik to name a few), starring alongside the likes of christian bale, cate blanchett and willem dafoe. but despite the subsequent flood of work, things weren’t as sunny as they seemed. “when slumdog happened it was just like high, high, high,” she says stretching her hand into the sky. “at some point it had to come down, right? sometimes when the start is…

text:
🌈
بهرام رادان توییت نوشته بود و از تاریخی بودن تغییر قوانین ازدواج در امریکا گفت
اول به او یورش آوردند که چرا چنین کرده است، توییت را حذف کرد. .
بعد به آنجا رسید که روزنامه‌ی کیهان علیه او نوشت، خواست ممنوع التصویر بشود و اینکه تصویرهایش را از خیابان‌های تهران پایین بکشند. هم‌زمان رادان را به یکی از دفترهای وزرات فرهنگ و ارشاد اسلامی بردند. .
آنجا هم حسابی ظاهراً ارشاد شده است و بلافاصله نامه نوشته است به حسین شریعتمداری و عذرخواهی کرده است. 
حالا قضاوت با شما.

اول به او یورش آوردند که چرا چنین کرده است، توییت را حذف کرد. .
بعد به آنجا رسید که روزنامه‌ی کیهان علیه او نوشت، خواست ممنوع التصویر بشود و اینکه تصویرهایش را از خیابان‌های تهران پایین بکشند. هم‌زمان رادان را به یکی از دفترهای وزرات فرهنگ و ارشاد اسلامی بردند. .
آنجا هم حسابی ظاهراً ارشاد شده است و بلافاصله نامه نوشته است به حسین شریعتمداری و عذرخواهی کرده است. 
حالا قضاوت با شما.

text: #metoo इस सिंगर ने काम देने के बदले 15साल की बच्ची से किस मांगा था। सिंगर श्वेता पंडित ने ट्विटर पर अपनी मीटू स्टोरी शेयर करते हुए अनु मलिक पर यौन शोषण का आरोप लगाया है। उन्होंने बताया कि कैसे अनु मलिक ने उनसे काम देने के बदले किस की मांग की थी। श्वेता ने अपनी पोस्ट में बताया कि यह सब साल 2001 में हुआ था, जब वह सिर्फ 15 साल की थीं। इतनी कम उम्र में उन्हें इस तरह के शॉकिंग एक्सपीरियंस से गुजरना पड़ा। उन्होंने कहानी शेयर करते हुए लिखा, 'यह मेरा मीटू है। मैं यंग लड़कियों को अनु मलिक से आगाह रहने की हिदायत देती हूं। और अब सोना महापात्रा ने कुछ दिनों पहले #metoo मूवमेंट के तहत कैलाश खैर पर यौन शोषण के आरोप लगाए थे। इस दौरान उन्होंने अनु मलिक के बारे में भी बात करते हुए उनके महिला सिंगर्स के प्रति अजीब व्यवहार के बारे में जिक्र किया था। उन्होंने इस ओर भी इशारा किया था कि अनु मलिक महिलाओं से सेक्शुअल फेवर पाने की कोशिश करते हैं। अब अनु मलिक पर एक और महिला ने आरोप लगाया है। #anumalik #metoo #metooanumalik
name: Uvayu

text:
this is lauren o'connor, who helped topple harvey weinstein and expose his rampant sexual abuse—but has remained largely behind the scenes until now. in her first ever television interview, she spoke with us at sundance about what happened: o’connor was a literary scout at the weinstein company who worked closely with weinstein. on a work trip, a distraught young woman knocked on o'connor's hotel room door in the middle of the night, saying she had just been assaulted by harvey weinstein. o'connor decided to risk her career—and potentially her life—and report his abusive behavior to hr at the weinstein company. she penned an internal memo outlining numerous sexual harassment and misconduct allegations, which later became the bedrock of the 2017 new york times investigation that exposed weinstein’s decades of abuse. she tells her own story for the first time in “untouchable,” a damning documentary that premiered at the sundance film festival on friday. we're broadcasting from sundance all week—you can see this full interview on tuesday's show. 
#metoo #harveyweinstein #sundance

text_retweet:
/ perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks /
.
pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.
.
pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya atau gerakan #metoo yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.
.
pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, “pertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai ‘amanah’ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa ‘kontrol seksual’ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.”
.
kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah.
.
“menjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,” ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019).
.
.
——

.

text:
mgtow 101: "every body wanna be like mike"
👂
👂
facebook went online about 2004-2005. i was in 10th grade when it became popular. when i created my profile i was 14 years old. i chose the name mike lowery as a my profile name, because it was who i wanted to be like when i grew up. i didn't randomly start viewing marriage this way.
👂
👂
i didn't know female nature at the time but through my experiences, i certainly know now. knowing female nature and learning mgtow, it seemed like the only pathway for mike lowery to walk. i knew early on, that mike had the better lifestyle than marcus.
👂
👂
mike had multiple women, a nice miami condo, a porsche, money in the bank, a career with a pension and he was fly every time he stepped out. marcus on the other hand, had a messy house, a nagging wife, a jalopy for a whip, a bunch of hard headed kids and to top it off he will probably face divorce later on in in bad boys part 3 or 4.
👂
👂
most men go mgtow because of life experiences, while others simply saw from the beginning that societies definition of a man wasn't for them.
👂
👂
fortunately if you aren't married you still have the chance to make a choice. i believe bad boys was one of the best movies to portray a beta vs alpha, simp vs mgtow lifestyle. i want every man to watch bad boys part one, study it, absorb it and ask yourself who do you want to be like marcus or mike lowery.
👂
👂

text:
#whitewednesdays majid azizi is a courageous man living in iran 🇮🇷 who could not stand by while the women of iran were attacked and abused by the corrupt oppressive authoritarian fascist regime of #alkhameinei and tinpot wannabe dictator #hoseinrohani . this man was jailed for supporting the women of iran and the #nocompulsoryhijab movement. the women will prevail over this criminal evil regime. democracy is fragile and must be fought for and protected. #freehijabprotesters #walkingunveiled #scanning #shepersisted #girlsofrevolutionstreet #girlpower #metoo #timesup #resist
براي برادرم #مجيد_عزيزي ‎نامش مجید عزیزی است. تنها یک هفته بعد از اولین دختر خیابان انقلاب روی کاغذی نوشت دختر خیابان انقلاب کجاست و شال سفیدی را در حمایت از او به چوب بست.
او اولین مردی بود که به خیابان رفت. هفته دوم باز هم رفت و‌ اعتراض مدنی‌اش را تکرار کرد تا اینکه کم کم خیلی ها به او ملحق شدند.
او در شهر شیراز روی سکو رفت و سرانجام بازداشت و دادگاهی شد، امروز ۲۸ آبانماه به زندان #عادل_آباد  برای گذراندن یک سال حبس تعزیری برده شد . ‎مجید کارشناس بازیگری سینماست آیا پاسخ اعتراض مدنی او این بود که پس از باز داشت و ضرب و شتم توسط نيروهاي انتظامي و امنيتي، به جرم تبلیغ علیه نظام به یک سال زندان محکوم شد و دادگاه تجدید نظر هم این حکم را تایید کرد و در دادگاه با دستبند جلوی چشم مادر نگران و خانواده جهت اجرای حکم یک ساله به زندان عادل آباد شیراز رفت.
#مجید_عزیزی در صفحه اینستاگرام خود پستی گذاشت و نوشت من نمیتوانستم در برابر ظلم ستم تبعیض علیه زنان سکوت کنم. مجيد عليرغم بيماري قلبي بر اساس تصميم مسئولين زندان از دريافت دارو محروم است. ‎ماهم صدای مجید میشویم و سکوت نمیکنیم. 
#girlsofrevolutionstreet 
#freedomartists ‏#nottoforcedhijab #saraamiirrii # #feminist🕊 #halehrostami ‎
خالق این اثر هنری زیبا دوست هنرمندم سارا جان 
@saraamiirrii 
#ساراامیری #هاله_رستمی

⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the assembly subsequently asked ambode to appear before it within one week over the 2019 budget, which has caused disagreement between the two arms of government.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
ambode had sent the 2019 budget to the house in december against the tradition of laying the budget before the house.
do you think there is a legitimate claim for impeachment or this is just another political propaganda?
.
.
.

text_retweet:
this is my friend, lauren. she’s brave af and i’m so proud to know her. harvey weinstein has become a symbol in the #metoo movement making it easy to forget he’s still walking free #noisacompletesentence repost from @democracynow this is lauren o'connor, who helped topple harvey weinstein and expose his rampant sexual abuse—but has remained largely behind the scenes until now. in her first ever television interview, she spoke with us at sundance about what happened: o’connor was a literary scout at the weinstein company who worked closely with weinstein. on a work trip, a distraught young woman knocked on o'connor's hotel room door in the middle of the night, saying she had just been assaulted by harvey weinstein. o'connor decided to risk her career—and potentially her life—and report his abusive behavior to hr at the weinstein company. she penned an internal memo outlining numerous sexual harassment and misconduct allegations, which later became the bedrock of the 2017 new york times investigation that exposed weinstein’s decades of abuse. she tells her own story for the first time in “untouchable,” a damning documentary that premiered at the sundance film festival on friday. we're broadcasting from sundance all week—you can see this full interview on tuesday's show. 
#metoo #harveyweinstein #sundance

text:
#tbt in the midst of these subzero temps, lookin’ back at the ol’ tv land days at a “price is right” wrap party. seen here, host bob barker and two of his legendary “barker’s beauties” show models who, at that time, were not allowed to speak on the show but were paid annual salaries of more than $100,000 per year. we taped two shows a day, m-w, three weeks a month from august through may. not a bad schedule for the money. the brunette had been hired as its first african-american show model and the blonde would go on to pose for the cover of playboy. in one of the first #metoo high-profile cases, two of the models on the show would later sue cbs-tv, alleging sexual misconduct by the venerable host. others claimed wrongful termination after being replaced by younger women. the network eventually settled all lawsuits out of court for undisclosed amounts.
🎥
.
.
.

text:
it all started with #weinstein. he had that kind of face that makes you hate him.
embodying #maleprivilege. one of those figures you look at and instantly say,
“it comes as no surprise, right?”
wrong.
women started to speak.
at first few of them, then more. and more.
hashtags. me too.
#metoo.
as if by bringing these two words together under a hashtag, we could finally claim a unified subject position. one, that is not split. #freud giggled.

text: the only time it is acceptable to lay a hand on someone. great, now that i have your attention, it seems to be that lately some people are getting way too comfortable with violating people (particularly females) as if we are merely objects. we are spoken about as if we are objects, treated as such as well. we’re be “grabbed by the p***y” called “a bitch” if we speak our mind, we are struck if we don’t agree to whatever it is you think. we are people with hearts, souls, and minds just like the rest of the world. we are not merely objects of adoration, sex symbols, and punching bags. we have visions, we have thoughts and ideas, opinions that differ. does not mean we can’t agree to disagree. it does mean however that we deserve respect and to be treated as a human being. hearing about domestic violence, whether it is mental or physical is disgusting and merely out right true work of a misled child who wasn’t raised properly. i am here for all of you, any of you, who have ever been through these times and feel they are alone. i am here for you #metoo i’ve also been a victim of abuse, but this is 2019. this is when we draw the line, and cut all ties to those who hinder our growth, let alone can’t keep their hands to themselves. i love you, you are loved and valuable, you matter and you are brave, strong, and an amazing individual. they try to control you because they don’t want you to see it for yourself. rise up anyways. raise your vibration, ask for help when you need it, it’s ok. put your pride aside, for the health of your own wellbeing. i love you, and it’s ok. #iloveyou #mental #physical #soultribe #peace #support #connection #youarenotalone

text:
“no” does not mean “convince me”. “no” means no. 
whether it’s because of all the romantic comedies we watch, or the way we’ve been brought up, many of us think that even if the person we like is not interested in us, we should keep trying. the ugly truth is that if someone doesn’t show interest, we aren’t supposed to chase them like lost lambs, hoping they’ll accept our love someday. we need to be sure enough of ourselves and have the dignity and consideration to let it go. rejections are a part of life. often, when we keep trying to make someone accept us, it is toxic for us and the other person. we feel like we are not good enough for them, or we end up making them uncomfortable and dislike us completely. rejections do not indicate your faults, but how you handle them says a lot about your character. the person rejecting you is not worth your time and effort. and the person rejecting you also has preferences, so unless they are abusive in the way they reject you, their actions are justified. if one persists when the other person is clearly not interested, it could be classified as a case of harassment. let it go. for yourself and others. it may not seem easy at first, but the first step is accepting your rejection, and the rest comes in time. 
good luck and keep blooming, 
s. 
#awareness #harassment #metoo #mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness

text:
nope, this is not the “10-year challenge,” because this before and after happened over a 1-year timeframe—1992 to 1993 to be exact. and i can thank the latest t.v. bachelor (“the virgin”) for this post.  i accidentally caught this past monday’s episode because my last client of the evening cancelled. i guess you could say it was meant to be because this episode took me back to 1992 when the bright-eyed, naive girl (pictured on the left)declared to the world (mainly my college campus) that she was a virgin and saving herself for marriage. as i share in my upcoming book, announcing to the world that you are a virgin (whether you are male or female), not only reeks of “i’m holier than you,” but it puts a target on your back for predators. over the next year, the girl with the half-closed eyes (pictured on the right) found that out the hard way. your virginity/sexual experience status is no one’s business but your own. and if you are saving yourself for marriage or abstaining for religious reasons...then keep it between you and god. still not convinced? well, read my soon-to-be-released book--click the link in bio 👆to preorder. #victorious #vday ❤️

text: ✍🏾poesia // gisela casimiro é uma fotógrafa e poetisa portuguesa, nascida na guiné-bissau. em 2017, por conta dos seus textos publicados em portugal e na turquia, ela foi poeta convidada no ‘international young writers meeting’ e apresentou a sua obra em istambul, konya e gaziantep. no seu primeiro livro de poesia, ‘erosões’ (lançado pela editora brasileira urutau), @giselacasimiro aborda “o desgaste do corpo, a destruição das relações, a morte, o afastamento, a perda. no entanto, até estas destruições parecem sofrer o poder da erosão, porque após a leitura não é o seu gosto que fica, mas o da cicatrização e das luzinhas que nos encaminham para a reconfiguração”, segundo comentário de andré tecedeiro. para ler hoje.

text:
возможно, ты уже читала историю журналистки анны карабаш: в мае 2017 года ее изнасиловал сотрудникотеля six senses zil pasyon на сейшельских островах. с тех пор анна добивается справедливости от руководства знаменитой сети. ниже история от первого лица.
.
меня зовут анна. я журналист с 20-летним стажем, живу в москве, воспитываю сына.
.
4 мая 2017 года меня жестоко изнасиловал сотрудник отеля six senses zil pasyon на сейшельских островах. это случилось во время рабочей поездки.он напал ночью, угрожая мне ножом, когда я спала в своей комнате. я никогда не видела этого человека раньше. я не знаю, как он зашел в мою виллу. он сказал, что пришел изнасиловать и убить меня... я действительно думала, что той ночью умру.
.
мне удалось сбежать только спустя 2 часа. я пыталась найти помощь, в течение 40 минут. наконец, я нашла одного из сотрудников и смогла сообщить об изнасиловании руководству six senses.
.
то, что случилось после этого, было похоже на еще одно изнасилование.
.
менеджмент отеля допрашивал меня в самых неприятных подробностях, игнорируя просьбы позвать полицию и врача. несмотря на наличие доказательств, владельцы отеля все еще пытаются замять дело.
.
произошедшее глубоко травмировало меня. я продолжаю проходить курс посттравматической терапии. прошло уже почти два года, однакосправедливый суд над преступником до сих так и не состоялся. мое дело все откладывается, доказательства исчезают.
.
я требую, чтобы pegasus capital advisors, владельцы six senses hotels resorts spa, взяли на себя ответственность, прекратили покрывать изнасилование и обеспечили полное и честное расследование моего дела.
.
📝пожалуйста, подпиши мою петицию. для того, чтобы судебное заседание не отменили или не отложили снова, нужно, чтобы петицию подписали как можно больше человек.
.
движение #metoo и #timesup вдохновило меня и дало силы, я здесь, чтобы сказать: пришло время выступить против изнасилования женщин в отелях.
.
👉полная история и ссылка на петицию – в сторис.

  indeed.   
   
 💛

please tag your friends to spread the word! nominations are now open for the 2nd annual #cbctrailblazers awards! (🔊 radio clip with dayna in our bio’s link!)
➖
help shine a light on an amazing individual who deserves recognition for the awesome work they’re doing to make ottawa a better place. ❤️
➖
also, big news! @cbcottawa has chosen dayna as one of the judges for this year’s nominees! she’s beyond excited.
➖
as you may remember, @daynaandherdogs was honoured (and surprised) last year to be recognized as one of ottawa’s inaugural #cbctrailblazers for her work as president of #safepetottawa, a local organization that helps find foster homes for pets so that abused individuals can leave their situations and get the help they need.
➖
a special thanks to #cbcottawa for having dayna on the ottawa morning radio show this week to talk about how receiving the honour impacted her and the charity she runs (audio link in bio). 👉 clarification from the interview: dayna is not the founder of safepet ottawa, but serves as its proud president.
➖
nominations are open until february 10 at www.cbc.ca/trailblazers
➖
thanks for helping us spread the word! 🎉 best of luck to all of this year’s nominees.

text:
it breaks my heart to share that on january 28th 2019 kim bok dong grandmother passed away at 93 years old ... i first met her in 2010, both grandma gil and grandma kim lived together at 'our peaceful house' a shelter for survivors of military sexual slavery during wwii. it was through their relationship would i learn how incredibly courageous, supportive and tough grandma kim was. she was in many ways an older sister to grandma gil... she gave me the nickname 'stick fly or fly stick' cause  my english name in korean sounded like that... i had the honor to travel with her to japan and glendale california for the statue reveal, it is through these journeys where i got to see first hand the legend and legacy of grandma kim. since 1992 when she first spoke out to the world about the atrocities committed against her and hundreds of thousands of other young women, she was laying the foundation to what we may now know as the #metoo movement. grandma kim has since dedicated her life to making a change for all of us... thank you  kim bok dong halmoni for your strength and wisdom. we will never forget. <3 .
.
.
#ibelievesurvivors #grandmother #fighter #resilience #nextgeneration #taiwan #og #documentary #activist #courage #bravery

text: whoa. i just survived a 7 day jury trial on a 7 count sexual assault case with a black male defendant and three white female complainants. the twelve jurors duked it out for 7 days from 9-430pm in a windowless room without any breaks. as you can imagine this was a super intense discussion in the me too era + all the racial tension in this country. that jury trial felt like a microcosm of all the problems in the world. there were full scale fights in that room that required the court security to step in. some people were logical, more people were emotional. everyone was opinionated. we found the defendant not guilty on 2 charges and we were undecided on the other 5 counts so the judge declared the case a mistrial. i hope we came to the correct verdict for all parties involved. all i know is that although i’m exhausted, i now secretly want to be a criminal defense attorney. 😂#metoo #juryduty #civicresponsibility #dotherightthing

text:
m e e t  t h e  c a s t
two 🌸 shelby 
played by 👩‍🦱 amanda vanosdol
“my favorite thing about shelby is that despite her illness and health issues she still manages to be a sassy pain in the ass. she’s amazing!

the most rewarding part of being part of this play has been creating my own strong bonds with the incredible women in our cast and crew. we laugh through every rehearsal and i’m so lucky to have my own group of steel magnolias now! 
i love this play because these women are there for each other through marriages, divorces, babies and even bad hair days. i love the juxtaposition between the humor in life and more serious matters and how the two can happen simultaneously, just like in real life.” tickets available on our website, link in bio! .

text:
the challenge i have for you all will enrich your soul beyond belief.🤔 february is #blackhistory month.👍🏾 find the unsung heros in your family - record them. 
their stories will be so rewarding; - you will learn so much about yourself and your family.

your children will learn - 😍

no texting! talk to your family.... yeah... that means -- on the phone or go see them. 
if they're not here anymore and you desire... share their legacy. give them a voice to share their triumphs in life.

enjoy..... one day they will be gone.

if i can help you in any way please let me know;)💋

text:
друзья!😎 на этой неделе вы могли задать свой вопрос победительнице первенств европы и чемпионатов россии, бронзовому призеру первенства мира по настольному теннису - марии тайлаковой @maariataylakova 💃
⠀
мы отобрали лучшие вопросы на которые ответил мария:
⠀
❓что делать, если тренер всячески * не замечает * твоего ребёнка, особенно если и ребёнок с характером, не тихо мирно подчиняется, а через призму своего видения работает. другим родителям все рассказывает тренер подробно , обсуждает над чем работать, а тебе сухое* все нормально*? из личного опыта-не сталкивались с таким?
⠀
➡️«может не настолько ребёнок и хорош как вам кажется и тренер просто не видит в нем перспективы. ну или поменять тренера. сама не сталкивалась с этим.»
⠀
❓мария, как считаете, какую часть вашего теннисного образования вам дало время в самаре?
⠀
➡️«нахождения в самаре мне дало многое на том уровне.»
⠀
❓маша, как ты считаешь - почему в россии нет будущего у взрослого спорта? большое количество молодежи, которое достигло неплохих высот на мировой арене, не показывает и вряд ли покажет какие-то результаты во взрослых соревнованиях. есть ли мотивация у спортсменов, которые переступили порог 18+?
⠀
➡️«я думаю, что появляются другие интересы и теннис уходит на второй план. нужно самому себе поставить цель и добиваться ее, соответственно будет и мотивация.»
⠀
⭕️продолжение в нашей группе вконтакте (ссылка в шапке профиля)
⠀

#framed ! and ready to go 🙂 also available in prints here on my fine art america page https://fineartamerica.com/featured/beast-ii-melissa-peterson.html 
this painting is part of a(n unfinished) series as my response to personal events related to the #metoo movement. i don’t generally like explaining where my artwork comes from, but i get a lot of questions on this one. a lot of it is very personal, but i also think art should mean something different for every viewer and i don’t want to influence somebody else’s interpretation or emotional response.  #acrylicpainting #painting #surrealism #figurepainting

text: went to ibiza and everyone had their nipples out. i didn’t. i hate that even in a place where nudity is rightfully normalized i felt shame and fear. in other places, it seems nudity is not conflated with sexuality and neither are seen as “dirty.” i was with americans and there were probably plenty of muricans vacationing on that beach. my breasts are large, my nipples are pierced and americans have a sick love/hate relationship with female nudity. i didn’t want some sicko snapping a pic without my consent or attempting something that would leave him with a broken nose. i remember doing a photo shoot at 19 in a bikini. some middle-age creep wearing khakis and reebok’s walked about 10 feet away from me and started snapping polaroids. he wasn’t even trying to be sneaky. my 20 year old photographer couldn’t do much to fend him off. i guess that memory still bothers me. next time, i will experience that unabashed freedom, even if i have to fight for it. #ibiza #chicago #americansbelike #murica #freethenipple #herbodyherchoice #justdontbeaweirdo #letwomenlive #metoo #feminism

text_retweet:
repost @democracynow: "this is lauren o'connor, who helped topple harvey weinstein and expose his rampant sexual abuse—but has remained largely behind the scenes until now. in her first ever television interview, she spoke with us at sundance about what happened: o’connor was a literary scout at the weinstein company who worked closely with weinstein. on a work trip, a distraught young woman knocked on o'connor's hotel room door in the middle of the night, saying she had just been assaulted by harvey weinstein. o'connor decided to risk her career—and potentially her life—and report his abusive behavior to hr at the weinstein company. she penned an internal memo outlining numerous sexual harassment and misconduct allegations, which later became the bedrock of the 2017 new york times investigation that exposed weinstein’s decades of abuse. she tells her own story for the first time in “untouchable,” a damning documentary that premiered at the sundance film festival on friday. we're broadcasting from sundance all week—you can see this full interview on tuesday's show. 
#metoo #harveyweinstein #sundance"
name: Feminist Magazine radio KPFK
tweet_full:
repost @democracynow: "this is lauren o'connor, who helped topple harvey weinstein and expose his rampant sexual abuse—but has remained largely behind the scenes until now. in her first ever television interview, she spoke with us at sundance about what happened: o’connor was a literary scout at the weinstein company who worked closely with weinstein. on a work trip, a distraught young woman knocked on o'connor's hotel room door in the middle of the night, saying she had just been assaulted by harvey weinstein. o'connor decided to risk her career—and potentially her life—and report his abusive behavior to hr at the weinstein company. she penned an internal memo outlining numerous sexual harassment and misconduct allegations, which later became the bedrock of the 2017 new york times investigation that exposed weinstein’s decades of abuse. she tells her own story for the first time in “untouchable,” a damning documentary that premiered at the sundance film festival on friday. we're broadcasting from sundance all week—you can see this full interview on tuesday's show. 
#metoo #harveyweinstein #sundance"

text:
tutte le donne del mondo dovrebbero leggere questo saggio.
.
"siamo nel bel mezzo di una violenta reazione al femminismo (il libro è uscito nel 1991), che usa le immagini della bellezza femminile come arma politica contro il progresso delle donne: il mito della bellezza."
.
"quando le donne si sono liberate della mistica femminile della vita domestica, il mito della bellezza si è sostituito ad essa, per portare avanti la sua opera di controllo sociale."
.

text:
decide today that good enough is no longer good enough. .

simple, right? 
so why is it more people can’t make a decision to change? keep reading if you’re curious. ⬇️⬇️ .

so what i’ve noticed in my coaching career over the years is that it’s easy for people to “decide” they want something.  who doesn’t want something more. .

but the real decision happens when you “decide” to do the work to get you there. .

that’s the moment when the change starts to happen.  when you start focusing on the actions steps to move you forward to your goal. .

so decided today to fall in love with the “work” that moves you to the change you’re looking for. divorce yourself from the “feelings” and marry the “work”. .

that’s when you become unstoppable!  i know because i’ve accomplished some pretty extraordinary things in my life with nothing more than a high school education and only a burning drive inside me that knew i was “more than” the circumstances around me .

are you “more than?” what people see?  decide today to do the work to get you there. .

i’ll be here to cheer you on!

text:
@ocasio2018 talks about her attitude towards fear and speaking up as a freshman member of the 116th congress..
.
"it’s always intimidating to speak up in a new setting. in congress, we abide by strict rules of communication, particularly in committee. for example, you’re supposed to address the chair, and speak in the third person when referring to your colleagues. breaking these rules can have consequences small and large: not knowing how means you could lose precious speaking time, or miss an opportunity to make a point. opposing party members are always looking for the slightest slip-up to gum up process or make an example of you.
.
so yes, speaking up for the first time in this environment can be scary. here’s my trick: for a long time, i’ve used fear as a guiding light 💡 instead of a reason to turn off. emotions are information and data too, and fear is telling us something. for me, fear isn’t saying “go away,” fear tells me “this is new, and it *could* be dangerous. there are are stakes here.” but i’ve very frequently interpreted fear as a growth cusp. aside from some concrete fears, we often don’t know what we’re afraid of until we get there, and feel it. fear tells us how to grow. fear, like a lot of discomfort, forces us to choose: “do i do this, or not?” without fear, there is no courage. without fear, we don’t have the opportunity to prove ourselves in ways we never thought possible.
.
so while we often think of fear as a signal to retreat, it can also be the opportunity to leap."
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
here is the lovely and talented @k8kelton signing her works for sentry.
.
@cactusgallery is excited to be ending the run at our frogtown space with @k8kelton ’s note-worthy exhibit! our new space is tba.
.
sentry opens tomorrow folks, yes, tomorrow, friday, february 1st. *6-9p. i know, i know, it's different, but hey, why not?
.
for sentry, kate sought to literally elevate the brave #silencebreakers, by combining their faces with elements of her family’s czech architecture. for more info: https://gem.godaddy.com/p/eec7bd
.
our pal david will fill our space with sound once more and many of the works in the smaller rooms are discounted and ready to go home with you. oh, and mr. rudeboy will be around waiting for a pat or an empanada bit to fall, and maybe even an actor or two may pop in ~ and perhaps a naima sighting, so please join us for our last hurrah in frogtown!
.

text:
i am slowly learning that even if i react, it won’t change anything. it won’t make people suddenly love and respect me, it won’t magically change them. 
sometimes it’s just better to let things be, let people go, don’t fight for closure, don’t ask for explanations, don’t chase answers and don’t expect people to understand where you are coming from. 
instead work on yourself and your inner peace ✨ 
what a beautiful self love reminder 👏

text:
“[i] always felt a bit of a struggle with my placement in the concert scenario... it was always borderline uncomfortable to even make eye contact with the people on stage—cause i could always feel the assumption there. since i’ve become a photographer in those situations, the feeling has subsided a bit. because i guess now my ‘purpose’ in being there is ‘clearly stated.’” @andreiaartt 
she brings up two major issues here, women being uncomfortable because of sexual assumptions, and the anxiety to justify your position as a woman to help shield you from those assumptions. the former issue is gaining visibility ever since the #metoo movement picked up speed a year ago, yet there seems to have been very little change that filtered down to the local music scene... 👂click the link in our bio to read about demystifying the sexist bogeyman: the groupie ✍️ @emily_fender 🎨 @rici_illustrates

text:
today, all workplaces in india are mandated by law to provide a safe and secure working environment free from sexual harassment for all women. but this wasn't the case until in 2013 when the posh (prevention of sexual harassment) act came into existence, which was driven by the popular case of bhanwari devi, a rural level change agent, who in the year 1992 was engaged by the state of rajasthan as a sathin to work towards the prevention of the practice of child marriages. during the course of her work, she attracted harassment from men of that community. she reported this to the local authority but no action was taken, and she was subsequently gang-raped by those very men.
.
when this cased was presented before the supreme court of india as a pil (public interest litigation), the supreme court realised the need to recognize sexual harassment as a violation of women's fundamental right to equality, and that all workplaces / establishments / insitutions be made accountable and responsible to uphold these rights.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
hurra för västerås!
➖
eldsjälarna michael jonsson och tård wennerborg har startat upp en lokalgrupp för män i västerås.
➖
– vi vet att det här med mäns våld är ett nationellt och globalt problem så därför känns det kul att starta upp en sådan här verksamhet lokalt i västerås för de i området som vill engagera sig, säger michael jonsson till sverige radio p4 västmanland.
➖
tård fyller i:
➖
– definitivt ökade #metoo medvetandet kring allt som män gör och orsakar. det var i samband med det som jag kom i kontakt med män.
➖
sveriges radio p4 västmanland intervjuade michael och tård som även svarar på frågan om hur en kommer åt problemet med mäns våld mot kvinnor:
➖
– som man är det bra att börja med att se till sig själv. hur förhåller jag mig till andra män, kvinnor och de här normerna som finns i mitt liv? att börja reflektera själv och tillsammans med andra män tror jag är en ganska bra början för att sen kunna se de här strukturerna i ett större sammanhang.
➖
ni kan lyssna på hela inslaget via länk i vår bio. för er som vill engagera er i västerås nya lokalgrupp, skriv till vasteras@mfj.se.⭐️

text: okay so the good news is the energies cosmically will also be supporting this shift- more to come on this more hopeful energies! i promise i will create another post tomorrow that highlights the brighter side of this weekend, and trust me it’s going to help us move forward! as challenging as this may feel, trust the process now more than ever. those who have leaped, you got this- don’t be fooled by the amount of work it entails to get unstuck from old situations no longer serving you. the hardest part was leaping, but we are not even close to the complete shift. breathe, have fun, and stay healthy and sharp, allow your body rest, grief, and exercise. be proud of yourself and honor the changes and resistance to changes that are occurring within and without. for those that are still holding themselves back from that leap, you will find these energies to be more of a challenge, even feeling overwhelmed by it all. breathe, you still have the opportunity to change your path- we always do. it may be harder the more we dig our heels in, however, if you accept the things you can not change, and have the courage to change the things you can- healing will occur, and transformation inevitably follows. there is no right or wrong path- that’s the beauty of life. we just think there is. are we choosing to look at our past experiences as mistakes or lessons? the power is within us all to create a shift from fear to love. it is a collective need and the divide we see across the world and in our own country is a manifestation of this truth. light needs dark. dark needs light. offering compassion while being firm in our conviction to hold those that create harm to others accountable. change starts within. be the change you wish to see in the world (gandhi). and live and let live.

text:
this term first appeared or started being used around 12th century and it was mostly used to describe an unmarried woman. nowadays, we use it to describe someone who has not had any type of sexual activity. 
first: it is not biological. there is no biological way to determine someone's virginity because you can't tell if a male has ever had sex and a female body's hymen can break from wearing tampons, riding a bike, or it may have never existed in the first place. that's just the magic of biology. everyone's born differently. 
two: everyone has sex differently. not everyone has sex by inserting a penis inside a vagina so the heterosexual norm of "virginity" usually implies this. so does that mean gay men or women won't lose their virginity? what about people who are paraplegic or quadriplegic? 
three: the idea that this is something we can "lose" puts a lot of pressure on all of  us. it pressures young people when they hear all of their classmates are "doing it" and fear they are behind developmentally. it puts emotional harm to victims of rape and assault when the concept is placed in a pedestal and society now views them as a tarnished object which has lost something. let's be honest, the concept views one group as the winners and one group as the losers when it comes to virginity.

cari amici, adesso si che posso urlare a squarciagola la mia gioia nel pronunciare : vittoria‼️✌🏻ebbene si, avere un cancro metastatico non e’ una banale influenza, ci si sente un po’ come un equilibrista, sospeso  su un filo sottilissimo sempre in bilico tra la vita e la morte. ma ora si festeggia!!!🎉 il nuovo protocollo sperimentale, da poco in italia, messo a punto dal professore nonche’ direttore dell’ unita’ di oncologia senologica  dell’ istituto nazionale dei tumori pascale di napoli: michelino de laurentiis ,ha ottenuto risultati eccellenti!!! dopo tre mesi di terapia, la mia pet e’ risultata negativa🎉🎉dovro’ continuare a curarmi ma lo faro’ con una speranza in piu’ e con una voglia di vivere infinita!!🍀✌🏻✌🏻

#repost @taranajaneen (@get_repost)
・・・
i can’t express how proud i am of our new series of psas called ‘survivor stories’.
our team worked with the wonderful folks at @deutschinc and created this beautiful campaign in order to shift focus back where it belongs - on the people who actually said ‘me too.’ there are four in total. this one is close to my heart. so many men and boys have been left out of the conversation. we have to change that. 
please enjoy and feel free to share! 
#repost @metoomvmt @get_reposter 
we asked survivors to talk about their journeys to healing... and they agreed. we've taken care to limit graphic depictions. we are proud of the work, but please don't feel obligated to watch (or watch alone) as it may be too much. 
this is an anonymous survivors' story. many of us experience violence in our own communities and don’t find justice or healing in traditional ways. to anyone who has had the courage to speak up, and then let go... we see you. we hear you. we believe you. #metoo #survivorstories #youarenotalone #metoomvmt #webelieveyou #survivor #healingjustice #noshame

text:
today we released two more blog posts to the nightingale from nilsa rivera and rachel. read a little about each of their essays and then click the link in our bio to read the full blog posts! 
in nilsa rivera’s essay, “the word rape is made of tar”, rivera does the difficult work of dissecting the word “rape”-not entirely in its meaning but “the sight of the word, the visual, almost physical, three-dimensional representation of it”. with this essay, rivera hopes to encourage her readers to think deeply about how the intricacies of language can affect us. 
rachel is no stranger to awakenings as we are lucky enough have her multimedia piece, "complex trauma: a memoir” currently on display. now, we want to share her literary talents! her essay, “we need to break through the silence on abuses of institutionalized children”, explores the systematic abuse and sexual abuse of institutionalized people from both a personal and objective perspective. she recognizes that " the lack of public outcry, the state-sponsored abuse and even the murder of people with psychological disabilities is a pattern" and hopes that her essay will begin to break the silence surrounding this epidemic.
.
.
.
.
.
#chicagoart #chicagononprofit #chicagogallery #advocacy#survivorart #artsed#artwatchers #metoo#believesurvivors #metoomvmt #consent #creativewriting

text:
an athlete's silence

i am creating a voice for sexually abused athletes by breaking my silence and sharing my experiences that i faced as a springboard and platform diver. i need everyone's help. i have launched a kickstarter campaign to help with publication cost of the sequel to surface tension, entitled, out-cast: the hollywood years and the re-branding of surface tension so they can be released at the same time. the campaign runs for a limited time, 15 days left. if we can get 650 people to donate $10, we will reach the goal and everyone will receive an e-book as soon as it is published. there are other donating levels, please see the link below. 
https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/john-michaellander/out-cast-the-hollywood-years?ref=project_build&fbclid=iwar3q7px2faozb899kuxjbjs3urskhnw_u7tleov7ya7dezwnpknhfsfixig

this book will continue following the main character, david matthew, and the effects sexual abuse has on his everyday life as he tries to break into the entertainment business. i have decided to tell my story through david's eyes. this story extremely relevant to today with #metoo movement and issues facing us gymnastics and osu. but it tells the story from a male's point of view, which our society deems not to recognize as a real problem. i hope that you can help me promote my kickstarter campaign. 
surface tension is available on amazon, and i have shared my story, "an athlete's silence" at tedxdayton 2018:

https://www.amazon.com/surface-tension-john-michael-lander-ebook/dp/b071zqmybn/ref=sr_1_2?crid=3bqi2wmyluogc&keywords=john-michael+lander&qid=1547994106&sprefix=john-michael%2caps%2c136&sr=8-2  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1-4yh82pqia

i am extremely passionate about helping survivors recognize the effects of abuse later in life.  i have been talking with safe sport, army of survivors, and breaking the silence. i would love to include you and/or business in helping me reach the kickstarter campaign goal so i can share my story and my passion of helping others recognize the long-term effects of sexual abuse.

#sexabusesurvivor #sexabuse
#fightsexabuse
#athlete #metoo
#metoomovement #breakthesilence #safesport #safespaces4youth

text:
thank you to everyone who attended last night’s waye talk. what 👏🏽 a👏🏽 night👏🏽
an absolutely packed room full of millennials ready to learn about the future! we dove headfirst into the intersection of technology x data x relationships, exploring everything from the impact online dating has had on racial diversity to the impact that virtual reality, artificial intelligence, and gene editing will have on relationships. how has #metoo impacted your company’s mission and strategy? how are you ensuring that your businesses are being built on the right side of history?  what defines a compatible match according to your algorithms? and what dating from us are you using to infer that? when amazon’s alexa starts providing dating advice in 2021, what does that mean for us? what will that future look like? these are just a few of the questions we asked last night’s thought-leaders... and we can’t wait to share the answers over the next week! the biggest thank you to our amazing panelists: @hinge ceo justin mcleod, @kairoshq ceo and former @tinder vp @ankurjain2 and @dateworkinghq founder @stevenmdean . last night’s conversation sparked such excitement for the future and reassurance that those who are laying the foundation for the digital future are doing so on the right side of history! 📷 @set3prod

text:
si escorpio hace referencia a todas  aquellas emociones intensas que se encuentra debajo de la superficie, tauro alude a todas las sensaciones que están “a flor de piel”.
.
continuamos analizando los ejes que conforman los signos complementarios en la rueda zodiacal.
.
todos llevamos energía tauro y escorpio en nuestra carta natal. que es otra manera de decir que todos podemos aprender a detectar y manejar estos conceptos en nuestra vida.
.
primero recordemos que son dos extremos de un mismo espectro. dos caras de la misma moneda: intimidad y placer, ambición y perseverancia, empoderamiento y valor.
.
si lees los dos artículos previos puedes aprender más sobre el alcance de ambos conceptos.
.
escorpio es lo profundamente psicológico, tauro la realidad que se percibe de manera tangible a través de los cinco sentidos.
.
saber en qué área de nuestra carta caen nos ayuda a saber qué áreas de nuestra vida se ven bañadas por dichas perspectiva.
.
saber que significan los planetas que se encuentran en esos signos nos ayuda a saber que otras excepciones y puntos de vista tenemos sobre esos asuntos.
.
por eso es tan importante conocer nuestra carta natal. solo asi podemos llegar al nivel de especificidad que los horóscopos no pueden garantizarnos. cada cabeza es un mundo, cada perfil astrológico es único, sobretodo en la manera de experimentar cada aspecto.
.
el año pasado júpiter (cuyos tránsitos se han visto asociados a procesos de expansión) hizo su paso por escorpio haciendo de la introspección la manera recomendada para el crecimiento personal esa temporada. además nos hizo adentrarnos y expandir nuestras mentes sobre temas de poder y sexualidad (recuerdan el #metoo y #timesup ? ).
.
este año urano (quien marca la pauta de la innovación) entra formalmente a tauro, por lo que se espera que empiecen cambios fuertes en los sistemas de valores (ej: la economía), pero los procesos de urano son más largos. más adelante podemos hablar más de astrología social, si les interesa díganlo en los comentarios.
.
por ahora, bienvenido al comeback de astral surf. you were deeply missed, pequeño saltamontes. i hope you like whats next.🔥
.
(imagen de kostis fokas vía pinterest).

text:
on march 3, 2018, i was a 2nd-year jet program assistant language teacher (alt) in sasebo, nagasaki, japan. my priorities at the time were simple: enjoy japan while i could. it was my last year on the program and i only had four months left before i returned to the u.s.
my assailant was a 4th-year jet alt from london. he was everyone’s friend, the fun guy at the party, a mentor/sempai in our community. while i was still struggling to learn basic japanese, he excelled in three years to conversational fluency. 
#jetprogram #jetprogramme #metoo #wetoo #saseboanon #私がエビデンス #私もエビデンス #女性差別 #standupjapan
hashtags: #JETProgram, #JETProgramme, #Metoo, #Wetoo, #Saseboanon, #私がエビデンス, #私もエビデンス, #女性差別, #StandUpJapan

my assailant was a 4th-year jet alt from london. he was everyone’s friend, the fun guy at the pay, a mentor/sempai in our community. while i was still struggling to learn basic japanese, he excelled in three years to conversational fluency.

on the day of my assault, we were preparing a song for an upcoming english camp. i had known my assailant since i first arrived in japan and always had fun talking to him. that day at lunch, our conversation revolved around trivial things. i talked about how i was dating someone long distance and he told me about how he was building his marketing portfolio to expand into a field beyond teaching english.

text:
i love my friend @plexxaglass so much and she just debuted a powerful new music video she directed for her song "ana thema” over at @ghettoblastermagazine. please watch!

her words:
“i was visited by a ghost, but not in the way you'd think; this wasn't your traditional haunting. the #metoo movement was fresh on everyones’ minds — i'd come forward about my experience with an ex-boyfriend from my high school years. then ana came to me, dressed in turn-of-the-century garb, pale as a ghost, in what i can only describe as a lucid dream, and she told me her story. we were by the sea and she was about to drown herself. she made me promise to tell her story, so that's what i've done here. and hey, it could've been just a dream, this story could be fiction, but i think we can all agree that it's not at all unfamiliar.”

gracias por tus "likes", pero sobre todo por portarte bien👼si quieres saber más, lee mis novelas🕵buscad la belleza, es la única protesta que merece la pena en este asqueroso mundo (r. trecet)🍀 si pinchas en este enlace verás cómo me presenta la editorial mito: https://mitoeditorial.blogspot.com/p/autor-invitado.html 👋😹👍🐩💫puedes leer artículos míos en el apartado "colaboradores" de diario alhaurín y en 101 málaga, así como en las revistas culturales guatiní (miami) y mimeógrafo (méxico). también me presentaron en la ventana del arte (la guía más completa sobre exposiciones en españa), revista one stop y en webs y blogs como: munduky y repoelas (ambas españolas) y, en inglés, en art reveal magazine https://go.shr.lc/2u3tk4e 🍹🎻🎶🦄💰💂 📚mis novelas llegan a cualquier lugar 🗺 desde: 
my novels arrive everywhere from

http://www.bubok.es/autores/bokusu
pincha el enlace en mi perfil.

verás que están en papel; que puedes leer las primeras páginas, algunas críticas y más... la 1ª también en formato digital. son para mayores🔞you can click the link in my profile. you'll see they are in paper, you can read the first pages, some critics and more... the first one is also for ebook, your computer, etc. they are for adults✌😘✊ todo lo ocurrido desde que decidí publicar y más en: http://www.margaritabokusumina.blogspot.com 💻puedes seguirme además en youtube, fb (2 perfiles, uno más usado que el otro, y una página de autora), en twitter y soundcloud 🎤(otros 2 perfiles, uno de ellos con más de 30 grabaciones en español, inglés y francés macarrónico)📲 gitano si me kisieras/okuparía en graná/la mejor kueva ke hubiera💃

text: an excerpt from the book “the emotionally destructive marriage”.. this is an important topic, one of the most important. it has been proven that after years of abuse the victims at some point usually turn from “just taking it” to “giving it right back.” totally normal. the does not mean you are the abuser or that you are the narcissist!!!! the only thing this means is that your mind has had as much as it can take and is responding to the abuse aggressively. this is when you need to get out because it only takes one fight to put you in jail, only one recorded fight to prove “you’re the crazy one”.. when you start fighting back and displaying mirrored behavior it is time to leave before it’s too late. this happened to me. i gave him fuel for his “she’s the crazy one” argument. i’m not proud of my behavior but it is literally a fight or flight reaction- a biological response to danger we all have. once you stop fleeing you start to fight back. don’t take yourself down to their level, don’t get in the mud with them. you are pearls- don’t get in the pig pen. #victimsyndrome #ptsd #fightorflight #fightbackbyleaving #pearlsandswine #domesticviolence #narcissisticabuse #verbalabuse #psychologicalabuse #emotionalabuse #metoo #childabuse #everyabuse #livinginfear #eggshells 🗣👩‍🦰🤯🤬

text:
my time and happiness is the most important thing in my life now.  i work a full time job, that i love going to daily.  i run a side business doing what i love to do. i have my nights free after 4pm on the weekdays and my weekends free.  that gives me a lot of time to spread out with my family, my side business and time for myself.  i wouldn’t trade that for any amount of money. not even a million dollars to have all of that taken from me.

value your time.  you can do what i do and be happy.  you can run a side business in marketing and work full time and still have time with your family and for yourself. 
we all meet the minimum requirements to succeed in life.  its what you do with it and how you do it for you to succeed.  the struggle i can guarantee you’ll have, but without that, you will not succeed!
#metoo
#loveyourself
#youcan
#youareenough
#pathwayscoretraining
#mystory

text:
"how to stop shoulding on yourself" --> the "s" word live (making sales simple & fun)

i am sharing with you something that has been coming up quite frequently with my paying clients and today there is a lively conversation going on about this very thing in my free facebook group.

goal: consider these 3 things so that you can avoid
burnout
overwhelm
going out of business 
questions: 
do you know anyone who puts a ton of pressure on themselves?

have you ever heard a friend, relative or your inner mean girl say out loud "you know what you should do"? do you find yourself having a neverending "to do" list?

#metoo

i have been in charge of my own schedule for over two decades. speaking from the perspective of having messed this part up a lot . . . i am sharing 3 things to consider when we feel like we should be doing this ... or that ... or something else.

1. the task fits the time.

2. consider the daily rhythms like a waldorf preschooler. 
3. give yourself some grace. you are only one person.

give yourself an #attagirl

take a moment and see what you have accomplished this past two days, two weeks, two months . . . you are incredible. 
let's continue the conversation --> https://m.me/renee.hribar?ref=convo

i have been in charge of my own schedule for over two decades. speaking from the perspective of having messed this part up a lot . . . i am sharing 3 things to consider when we feel like we should be doing this ... or that ... or something else.

1. the task fits the time.

2. consider the daily rhythms like a waldorf preschooler. 
3. give yourself some grace. you are only one person.

give yourself an #attagirl

take a moment and see what you have accomplished this past two days, two weeks, two months . . . you are incredible.

text:
um ano depois do #metoo, o jornal o público foi saber como vai o feminismo em portugal, juntamente com 4 feministas sensacionais, e eis que se explora toda esta questão da desigualdade de género. 
começando pela inclusão e (in) justiça, relembram que a luta feminista não se faz sem um combate à precariedade, ao racismo e à fobia-lgbti.

vale rememorar que o feminismo, para além de um movimento é a luta constante por direitos iguais e por uma sociedade mais igualitária, onde mulheres deixarão de ser desvalorizadas ao ponto de surgirem certas frases como “estava de minissaia, portanto estava a pedi-las”. onde todas poderão sair à rua sem que o medo de serem violadas ou assediadas as persiga e onde as nossas vestes ou estado de espírito não nos comprometa em tribunal.

#feminismo #inclusão #justiça #direitos #portugal #metoo #somosblergh #blergh #batatas #vivaabatata

text:
step in please 💄
“can you hear me now?” -sound piece voicing anonymously collected experiences of sexual harassment. the stories are retold by male voices, to include men in the conversation and to reach men, as studies show that men still find male voices more convincing than female voices. we’ve been telling these stories again and again. being heard and being heard are two different things. the piece highlights that women and femmes don’t have to chance to not get sexually harassed or violated, toxic masculine culture does.
welcome to the opening tomorrow at 7pm at the kunsthal charlottenborg spring exhibition. 🥂
#didnotaskforit #sexualharassment #feminism .
