text:
have you spotted our tarc ads around town? post and tag us if you do! help spread the word about our tarc’s ride to safety program which provides free transportation for anyone who needs to get to the center for women and families.
=========================
get onto any tarc bus in louisville or southern indiana and tell the driver you need a ride to safety. you do not need money or a tarc ticket; the ride is free. the driver will arrange for a tarc employee to meet the bus somewhere on its route who will transport you in a car to the center for women and families. you can use this free service if you’re by yourself or if you have your children with you.
==========================
for information on tarc stops and routes, visit www.ridetarc.org or pick-up a route schedule at one of the many information stands across louisville and southern indiana.

for more information about the center for women and families and the ride to safety program, call our toll-free crisis line at 1-844-237-2331.

text:
v a g i n a s | okay, let's talk vaginas! february is the month where i'm focusing my attention to supporting & minimising the impact of my #vulvodynia #vaginismus - something i developed after being raped & after have a very intense trigger during sex - so i can bang more often.

so what is it? vulvodynia is basically on going pain + discomfort in your vulva because it is constantly in a "fright or flight" mode. meaning that there's an increased amount of nerve-endings that are on a constant hyperactive loop. and should anything try to work it's way into my vagina, it's little opening muscles go into overdrive and won't budge (this also means that if the willy does get inside, it does not have a nice experience trying to get out). it also means it feels like burning fire should anything touch because it's not use to the bloodlfow. 
physical health & nutrition are factors that pull into it being less sore as it allows the muscles to relax & break their loop. i'm also seeing a pelvic floor physiotherapist who tries to help desensitise the tissue & muscles. there is no real cure, just these little bits that need to worked on daily.  i'll be focusing my attention to lower body & pelvic floor this month to try alleviate & get some bang times in.

questions?? ask me about it 👇

text:
mañana es viernes, pero ya tengo esta cara y estos pelos... así que ten "cuidaito" conmigo... ☝menos mal que me llegó esta crítica a mi 5ª novela: "hola, que le he dado a 'me gusta' y que sigo siendo fan. estoy leyendo la maga y me gusta tu escritura y los detalles como mensajes y demás en códigos coloquiales que sorprenden al releerlos. gracias margarita por esos murales de literatura para poder vivir en inocencia y en sabiduría del pueblo." :) (m. m.) 🍀 👋😹👍🐩💫puedes leer artículos míos en el apartado "colaboradores" de diario alhaurín y en 101 málaga, así como en las revistas culturales guatiní (miami) y mimeógrafo (méxico). también me presentaron en la ventana del arte (la guía más completa sobre exposiciones en españa), revista one stop y en webs y blogs como: munduky y repoelas (ambas españolas) y, en inglés, en art reveal magazine https://go.shr.lc/2u3tk4e 🍹🎻🎶🦄💰💂 📚mis novelas llegan a cualquier lugar 🗺 desde: nimy novels arrive everywhere from
http://www.bubok.es/autores/bokusu
pincha el enlace en mi perfil.

verás que están en papel; que puedes leer las primeras páginas, algunas críticas y más... la 1ª también en formato digital. son para mayores🔞you can click the link in my profile. you'll see they are in paper, you can read the first pages, some critics and more... the first one is also for ebook, your computer, etc. they are for adults ✌😘✊ todo lo ocurrido desde que decidí publicar y más en: http://www.margaritabokusumina.blogspot.com 💻

puedes seguirme además en youtube, fb (2 perfiles, uno más usado que el otro, y una página de autora), en twitter y soundcloud 🎤(otros 2 perfiles, uno de ellos con más de 30 grabaciones en español, inglés y francés macarrónico)📲 💃

thank you by meghan trainor
15 tracks / deluxe edition
2016
rating: 8,5/10
———————————————————————
i love meghan so much and i can’t understand why some people dislike her / her music, because i think she’s amazing! just like title she (co)wrote every song and even helped with producing them! i like the doo-wop style on here previous album more but this album is still very good. i love the fact that there are finally some more slow / sad songs on this album, which wasn’t the case with title. just a friend to you, hopeless romantic and kindly calm me down are just beautiful and i hate to see that they’re so underrated. so overall this is a very good album and i can’t wait for her next album, everybody stop sleeping on her! #tacmeghantrainor

text:
the first time i had a panic attack i was in the middle of my nutrition 101 class. ⠀
⠀
we were watching a video on cardiovascular health which showed rather graphic segments of an angioplasty. the room started to spin, not really an unusual feeling, i have condition called noncardiovascularsyncopy. which essentially means, sometimes gravity works against my system, and i pass out. it’s not rare, many people suffer from this, though i was told most people ‘grow out of it’ by the time they turn 18. i was 20 at the time. ⠀
⠀
i left the classroom: head spinning, heart pounding, stomach in my throat.. at least i wasn’t driving this time. lying down was suppose to help and though the hallway’s cold, musty tile felt like bliss, it wasn’t doing a thing to calm me. it was a panic attack.⠀
⠀
i would like to say it was the last one, but even six years later they are ongoing- though less frequent. learning what my triggers are has been the most helpful in learning how to control or anticipate when i may have one.⠀
⠀
it took me way too long to figure out one of my biggest triggers is heart health. i used to just say it “freaks me out” like i could do nothing besides call it an irrational fear but was it irrational? i looked deeper, and i realized i was so afraid because i was not taking control of myself and of my heart. now i focus my weight, i control what i put into my body, i do my cardio, i meditate. this is my time to be selfish and exhale the bullshit that i’ve been putting myself through. this is the time for me. ⠀

text:
hi everyone! there are a lot of new faces around here and i wanted to introduce myself for those who don’t know me yet. i am fabiana, an east coast girl living in a west coast world. i am a certified therapeutic recreation specialist (ctrs), entrepreneur, and wellness enthusiast. i also work for senior living company. 
i am 1 of 5 kids and the only girl. yeah i loved every minute of being the only girl! i married @williamgould82 about 2.5 years ago. we enjoy traveling, cooking together and using essential oils. we have and love our fur babies mandi-love and cali faith. 
i am passionate about working with seniors and helping them live their best life at this stage in their life. i am also very passionate about educating others on living a chemical free life to live a life above the wellness line. .
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#holisticliving #wellness #wellnessinsideout #agouldstory #fgnaturalwellness #selfcare #wellnesswednesday #metoo #healthyliving #healthyhome #healthyfamilies

#repost @misssey (@get_repost)
・・・
from the sasha center: “this model was designed to give service providers, funders and the community at large a model to understand and see the barriers that exist for black women who need sexual assault services. black women who disclose need to receive culturally specific services regarding rape and sexual assault for a full and integrated experience for healing.” this illuminating infographic created by kalimah johnson, sasha center’s executive director, is also relevant for those of us serving black women and girls who are survivors of commercial sexual exploitation. we cannot ignore or erase the systemic, gendered and racialized barriers that prevent and impede black women and girls from accessing support for the sexual violence they experience at disproportionate rates. we must work collectively to remove these barriers, create access, and ensure services are culturally appropriate.

text:
forum / picasso and #metoo at @agsa.adelaide 6-7pm tonight

adelaide peeps, this prescient forum is an event to crawl over hot sa pebble stones over to get to. 🔥 
twin maria zagala, associate curator prints, drawings and photographs will be joined by professor meaghan morris from the department of cultural and gender studies at the university of sydney (🙌🏻) in the auditorium to consider picasso’s practice in the context of the #metoo movement. the discussion begins with an iconographic reading of some of picasso’s prints in the vollard suite presented by emerita professor memory holloway, department of art history at the university of massachusetts. 
the show is excellent. then there are exciting little details. like although i’m not personally familiar with memory holloway’s work i can’t get over her name (👌 ). and since it’s first friday’s at the gallery there will be drinks and music. perfect. #agsa #picasso #metoo

text:
as national human trafficking awareness month comes to close, we’d like to remind you that there is still more work to be done. human trafficking happens every day, and not to just one type of person, and it happens in the places we least expect it. it’s up to us to stand up and fight against it to protect our youth. we have to fight against it because women and young girls deserve to be supported and empowered. they deserve an opportunity to go from victim, to survivor, to leader.
--
to learn more about how you become equipped to support and empower victims of human trafficking, attend our victim, survivor, leader™ (vsl) training, march 4th-5th  in nyc. also visit our site, gems-girls.org.
-
--
---

text:
don’t jump.🌻
today, wasn’t a very good day. but that’s okay. i went for a walk in a place i love, to calm down and reflect. and this, the fact that someone had stood on those cliffs and not just stared at the beauty of rest bay, but they thought of others. it made my heart happy. don’t jump. never give up. you are worth so much more than that. i love you. .
when you pass through the waters,
i will be with you;
and when you pass through the rivers,
they will not sweep over you.
when you walk through the fire,
you will not be burned;
the flames will not set you ablaze.
isaiah 43:2🌊⛰💙

text_retweet:
reposted from @lifeafternarc -  when working with #coaching clients there comes a beautiful moment where the client fully realises his or her own worth, & starts making some seriously self-honouring moves as a result. 🦋 .
.
.
they may literally wake up one morning & decide that -yes - they are going to press charges against the abuser after all. 
or they are going to file for divorce. 
or they’re going back to college. 
or starting that side business they always dreamed about. 
putting plans to move to a new location that nourishes their soul. .
.
.
or maybe it’s a more subtle but equally important breakthrough— such as a decision to block the abuser’s number. 📲 .
.
.
what have some of your major breakthroughs been since realising you’ve been abused by a narcissist?  these are achievements to be proud of, so let’s celebrate your progress. 💫 .
.
.
one of my very first steps in the right direction was way back when i applied for & was awarded a restraining order against the narc. .
.
.
another breakthrough was letting the police know about all the abuse the #narcissist subjected me to. and doing that also means that when the abuser's next victim calls law enforcement (and there is always a next a victim with these individuals) there will already be a record on file to help validate the new victim’s claims.  and the victim after that. .
.
.

the abuser's previous victim before me has said she wishes she'd reported him to police, too.  to document the fact that what he did to her is disgusting & unacceptable -- regardless of whether her complaint led to charges or not.
.
.
.
you?
.
.
.
#narcissisticabuse #breakingthesilence #solidarity #metoo #eachoneteachone #healingfromabuse #narcissisticabuserecoverycoach #lifeafternarc #outofthefog 🌪 - #regrann

text:
the backstreet boys have a new album out. it’s all over my twitter feed. a few years ago i would’ve been excited along with all the other fans. now i get a pit in my stomach, because all i can think about is my brave sister survivor @themelissaschuman. another trigger for her to have to endure. another reminder of her rapist & what he did to her. i know how painful it is for me to remember & relive my assault. i can only imagine how horrible it is for melissa because her rapist is famous & beloved.
today i went back and read her incredibly brave and vulnerable blog post. the post that gave her a platform to share her story. the post where she detailed the pain of the assault and the pain she’s lived with afterwards. the post that propelled her into the spotlight and made her a target for bsb fans. threats, hate mail, and even suspicious packages sent to her home. all because she told the truth.
on those bad days when i wish i would’ve never told anyone, i remind myself of melissa. her bravery and the bravery of every other survivor gives me the strength to go on. 
i long for the day when victims and survivors are no longer blamed for a crime committed against them. until then we will continue to speak out. you cannot silence our voices. we will not stop telling the truth.
#metoo #timesup #sexualassault #victims #survivors #hope

text:
most people confuse how they feel and how they think which makes them believe it is fact. this breeds assumptions and it creates bad decision making. it can exacerbate #depression #anxiety #bipolar and other #mentalillness but it can also vary from innocent assumptions to extreme violent situations.
..
as an example, i knew someone whilst in a psychiatric ward and we were watching a show on tv. an advertisement came on the television with a woman promoting a car company. this person said then that "she loves sex and wants sex", i asked how do you know that? they said "you can tell by her eyes"... i was so shocked... a less extreme example is a breakup situation, when someone believes there is still a chance because they don't want it to be over. it progresses into a deeper obsession with the person and can lead to domestic violence or stalking or other types of violence. ..
your feelings are not facts and your thoughts are not facts either. be aware of that and the fact others may believe how they feel and think is what is true even though it isn't. 👌🏻

text_retweet:
this is the first of four. please note, this will be triggering. #metoo #triggerwarning  #repost @taranajaneen with @get_repost
・・・
i can’t express how proud i am of our new series of psas called ‘survivor stories’.
our team worked with the wonderful folks at @deutschinc and created this beautiful campaign in order to shift focus back where it belongs - on the people who actually said ‘me too.’ there are four in total. this one is close to my heart. so many men and boys have been left out of the conversation. we have to change that. 
please enjoy and feel free to share! 
#repost @metoomvmt @get_reposter 
we asked survivors to talk about their journeys to healing... and they agreed. we've taken care to limit graphic depictions. we are proud of the work, but please don't feel obligated to watch (or watch alone) as it may be too much. 
this is an anonymous survivors' story. many of us experience violence in our own communities and don’t find justice or healing in traditional ways. to anyone who has had the courage to speak up, and then let go... we see you. we hear you. we believe you. #metoo #survivorstories #youarenotalone #metoomvmt #webelieveyou #survivor #healingjustice #noshame

text:
very few people know my story, know my traumas. i don’t share them often, not because they don’t deserve their truth being spoken, but because it makes others uncomfortable, and i’m a people pleaser. so i stay silent. what good does it do, though, to not show people all of me? my childhood, horrible as it was, is part of who i am, for better or worse. so here goes. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
❤️⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i haven't had an easy life. i was sexually abused for several years as a child, and emotionally and mentally abused for even longer, by my father. before this last year started, i had always lived my life according to how others told me i had to. i was ugly because i was told i was. i was unlovable because i was told i was. i wasn't wanted and would never be because i was told over and over that i wasn't in the first place. i was wicked because horrendous things happened to me and i didn't "do" anything to stop it, so i must have wanted them to happen. (to put it into perspective, i was seven when it started, and was, in my mind, taken from my mother and the only family i knew up until then). i deserved what i got because i was who i was, and it would never change. years of lies and harsh words can seriously damage your psyche, and it may never be healed regardless of how intelligent you are or how much you know better. i didn't deserve love, a good life, or good moments. this was the life i had to endure. my identity was wrapped around what someone else told me i was, so that identity was twisted and warped. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
❤️⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the person who is supposed to be your first line of defense is the one who is slowly killing you. i’ve grown into the person i am, and i am awesome in spite of him. ❤️⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
wise words from @elizabeth_smart_official
💞
a bill was introduced yesterday in our state to protect a child from an abusive parent. 977 children walked through the doors of our children’s advocacy center last year with reports of abuse. that is almost a thousand children in one small county of our state. this is a huge problem. @rainn says that the perpetrator of most child sexual abuse cases is a parent. according to @d2lorg only 19-29% of child sexual abuse reports even result in an arrest. @childhelp warns that this is a huge hidden epidemic.
✨
putting a child back into the care of an abusive parent can at the least lead to toxic stress and at the worst, as we see too many times in the news, lead to a devastating outcome.
✨
if you haven’t heard of the adverse childhood experience (aces) study, i’m attaching a link and hope you will learn more about it. basically it is adding up the harmful experiences a child has endured in their life and the higher the number the greater risk that child will have a multitude of problems later in life. arkansas has one of the highest ace scores in the nation. toxic stress associated with forcing a child to be with someone they are afraid of or could potentially hurt them will only add to our ace scores.
✨
we combat aces with trauma informed systems that you get by having trauma informed policies. having statewide uniform policies that inform and guide those involved in making decisions affecting a child ensure that no matter what the child’s zip code is and what court system they find themselves in, the child is protected.
✨
a parent should never be forced to hand over their scared child to the person that abused them. a child should never be afraid to go home, should never be afraid to go to sleep not knowing what might happen to them in the middle of the night, and they should never be afraid of the one person in the world that should protect them the most.
💞
https://www.acesconnection.com/
https://www.child-trends.org/publications/prevalence-adverse-childhood-experiences-nationally-state-race-ethnicity
#defendsurvivors #believeprotectdefend #cac #believethechild
name: Paula
tweet_full:
wise words from @elizabeth_smart_official
💞
a bill was introduced yesterday in our state to protect a child from an abusive parent. 977 children walked through the doors of our children’s advocacy center last year with reports of abuse. that is almost a thousand children in one small county of our state. this is a huge problem. @rainn says that the perpetrator of most child sexual abuse cases is a parent. according to @d2lorg only 19-29% of child sexual abuse reports even result in an arrest. @childhelp warns that this is a huge hidden epidemic.
✨
putting a child back into the care of an abusive parent can at the least lead to toxic stress and at the worst, as we see too many times in the news, lead to a devastating outcome.
✨
if you haven’t heard of the adverse childhood experience (aces) study, i’m attaching a link and hope you will learn more about it. basically it is adding up the harmful experiences a child has endured in their life and the higher the number the greater risk that child will have a multitude of problems later in life. arkansas has one of the highest ace scores in the nation. toxic stress associated with forcing a child to be with someone they are afraid of or could potentially hurt them will only add to our ace scores.
✨
we combat aces with trauma informed systems that you get by having trauma informed policies. having statewide uniform policies that inform and guide those involved in making decisions affecting a child ensure that no matter what the child’s zip code is and what court system they find themselves in, the child is protected.
✨
a parent should never be forced to hand over their scared child to the person that abused them. a child should never be afraid to go home, should never be afraid to go to sleep not knowing what might happen to them in the middle of the night, and they should never be afraid of the one person in the world that should protect them the most.
💞
https://www.acesconnection.com/
https://www.child-trends.org/publications/prevalence-adverse-childhood-experiences-nationally-state-race-ethnicity
#defendsurvivors #believeprotectdefend #cac #believethechild

text:
willow creek association releases resource on ministry and #metoo
#
chicago (rns) — there are a lot of abuse survivors who don’t feel safe in church — and a lot of abusers who do, the rev. dale ingraham of curtis baptist bible church in campbell, n.y., told a room of willow creek association staff and christian leaders last month. whether the abuse happened at home or in the church, congregations rarely address the topic, according to ingraham, who co-founded a nonprofit called  speaking truth in love with his wife, faith, to address the issue of abuse in the church. “i’ve really come to believe that one of the major reasons people are leaving the church is because of the issue of abuse,” he said.a video of ingraham’s remarks was published online this week, part of a series by the willow creek association called “ministry and #metoo: a learning journey for leaders.” filmed on willow creek community church’s main campus in south barrington, ill., the videos are part of the wca’s response to allegations of sexual misconduct and abuse of power by willow creek founder and former pastor bill hybels. hybels, who retired early in april from both the church and association, has denied the allegations, but both the church and wca since have…

text:
‪the media. me too. it’s all happening pretty fast, right?‬ ‪
‪
there’s no denying it. the media has had a huge presence in the emergence of the #metoo movement. so for the last day of the january deep dive into the post-show workshop, we’re talking about where it all began.‬ ‪

we also can’t believe that it’s been a whole month since we started airing these videos. it’s been such a joy to dive into what the post-show workshop is all about.

but if you’re craving more, come see the show for free tomorrow at @dramatistsguild. 7:30pm. 1501 broadway. 7th floor.

text:
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
“our greatest fear should not be of failure but of succeeding at things in life that don't really matter.”
-francis chan
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
when i asked god & goddess for clarity on why my passion for the feminine matters so much, they answered me in no uncertain terms.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
last night i had nightmares of a young girl raped, branded and cut with her rapists initials. reeled in by the promise of love.
-
i am the man who told her her story wasn’t valid.
i am the observer who didn’t protect her.
i am the young woman.
-⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
literal? yes. but it is also the metaphor so many of us are living every day.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
time is up!

text:
when we’ve experienced a trauma, starting over can feel like the a burden far too heavy to bear. .
.
but we can. you can. starting anew can happen every day, every hour, every second — if that is what’s needed. .
.
what does it mean to start over? does it ‘have’ to be a huge undertaking? if it feels like it, where did that expectation come from? .
.
a little less than 2 weeks ago, i was rear-ended on the freeway at a high speed. had i not been wearing a seat belt or left ample space between me and the car in front of me, i would have likely been severely injured or crushed between a semi truck and the cars immediately behind and in front of me. my nearly brand new car totaled. back and neck injured, but no broken bones. .
.
car accidents, job losses, deaths of loved ones, domestic and sexual violence, psychological abuse; these and more can be terrifying and traumatic events that leave us feeling paralyzed. what i think i did not realize personally is although i felt paralyzed, i was still making moves to put pieces back together. even if it was simply saying to a friend or loved one that i needed help or a shoulder to lean on. even if i took one extra deep breath for myself. i was starting again and kept moving forward. .
.
healing is not linear, and yours will not look like mine or anyone else’s. to anyone needing to read this today: starting anew is a moment by moment or breath-by-breath process if we need it to be. no one deserves your love and kindness more than you. .
.

text:
pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.
.
pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya atau gerakan #metoo yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.
.
pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, “pertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai ‘amanah’ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa ‘kontrol seksual’ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.”
.
kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah.
.
“menjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,” ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019).
.
.
——

text:
“i can’t stand feminists“

that was from a 17 year old girl at the gym.

her and her mother were debating the women’s movement. mum was coming from the old school & her daughter the new school.

then they turned to me sitting there sweaty after a class asking for an opinion on this matter.

mum was wagging her finger and daughter was getting wide eyed as the seconds ticked away. 
it was definitely a tough conversation to enter into.

so i entered into it... depends if the feminist is coming to help people become accountable for their actions or coming from a victim mentality looking for revenge.

a feminist victim is someone who hasn’t had a voice in childhood & so when challenged or pushed brings out that suppressed voice by rallying with others for support to something they haven’t dealt with in themselves. 
they come across as activist behind a cause fuelled by deep resentment.

they can hide easily because they usually stand behind some injustice that’s happened to them or to a group of people they’re associated with.

michelle obama is a healthy expression whereas the feminist victim gathers others to make themselves feel the power they missed out on having.

the cause can be admirable but all that hidden resentment can come flooding out when an opportunity presents itself for a person who has been persecuted ( victim). i’ve had 3 people in seminars pull the victim card out & because they’re not easy to spot only appear when they think an injustices has popped up they can evade detection. 
they once were the innocent child 
they once had a heart of love & pure light 
pushed down by the parent , teacher or guide 
now to become an unhealed victim 
resentful 
hidden behind a smile , an image or a cause but hiding deep pain & resentment.

goodie goods. 
all love and light hiding dark resentments usually with a lot of physical conditions that represent the resentments physically stored in the body.

to come back they must find their own power again and own it. to become the hero they lost long ago.

to bring the victim to the victor & overcome the need to destroy what held that love down.

and so we sat and talked debated & questioned until it was all too

i want things in my timing. quite frankly. but time after time i learn that life doesnt work this way...and god's timing is best. waiting means my faith, patience and trust are tested. i'm getting better at waiting, yet sometimes i have an adult temper tantrum lol. 
waiting on dreams to unfold is hard. waiting and working through healing and recovery is equally as hard. but it will happen. you just need to keep consistent and keep working on it.

still a queen 👑✊.

text:
#mirácomonosponemos #yotecreo #niunamenos #metoo

mi historia y las preguntas que me hacen cuando se enteran:

a partir de mis 4 años hasta los 10 años fui abusada sexualmente por "cachito g****" y "rolo su****", entre otros. ambos vinculados a la ex pan, cuando formaba parte de la fuerza aérea argentina. (no pongo los nombres completos porque lo que falta es que me quieran denunciar a mí.) muchos de mis abusos se dieron lugar en el aeropuerto de neuquén, así que gente de la zona por favor cuiden a sus chicos.

si tu primera pregunta es: ¿qué pasó? ¿qué tipo de abuso? ¿me podés dar más detalles?
¡te pido que deconstruyas! no tengo necesidad de seguir victimizándome todavía más. sin embargo, por suerte hoy no tengo miedo de contestar, me violaron de todas formas que se puede abusar a una mujer, pero no era una mujer; era una niña. te pregunto: ¿todavía tengo que ser más gráfica? ¿es necesario que sepas todo lo que me hicieron durante 6 años? ¿te cambia en algo la vida si describo un por menor de todo lo que sufrí?

si tu segunda reacción es: ¡ah! ¡entonces si fue algo grave! ¡te pido que deconstruyas! cualquier abuso es muy grave.

si sabes de derecho y me preguntas: ¿che y la denuncia? deconstruí, apenas pude empezar a reconocer y a hablar de lo que me pasó, me comuniqué con todas las personas que sabía que me podían asesorar legalmente (yo no veía que prosperara por temas de caducidad y prueba). la respuesta fue que no se podía hacer nada.
name: Geraldine Romina Brussa

text:
welp....i’m not going to say today #achalasia and #hashimotos won....but i will say they made life difficult.  my plan for today went out the window as soon as i woke up. correction: as soon as i overslept by 1.5 hours, missed my morning workout, and scrambled to get us ready for school/work 🥴. then drove 2 hours for an important meeting (which was successful btw), 2 hours back home, then worked from the trampoline zone so mini-me could get her exercise in, then back home to fix dinner and stay committed to my 20-minute commitment. i had intended to go to cf class today, but didn’t make it because it’s now 6pm and i’ve only managed to consume about 500 calories.
.
.
so, while it could have gone better, i still moved and did what i could. i also faced more fears - lateral jumping.  anyone who has seen me at the crossfit box knows i don’t/won’t do lateral jumps much. it’s a mind-over-matter thing and they are scary, hard, and terrible.  yet another weakness i’m working on. .
.
i’ll count today as a smiley face 😀 like we use at @crossfit_i1uvit when you try your best and that’s all we can ask for the day. not focusing on time, reps or rounds. just effort.  i count today as 1% better mentally, so that’s a win.
name: Bri | Female Empowerment Coach

text:
perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks
.
pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.

pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya. atau gerakan #metoo yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.

pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, “pertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai ‘amanah’ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa ‘kontrol seksual’ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.” kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah. “menjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,” ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019). pratma kemudian menjelaskan bahwa umat islam harus berupaya menegakkan syariat islam kaffah sebagai solusi persoalan kekerasan terhadap perempuan, “tidak kalah penting mengedukasi umat bahwa persoalan kekerasan seksual, bahkan pelecehan kehormatan perempuan tak akan terjadi jika khilafah tegak. syariat kaffah itu memiliki hukum yang amat memuliakan manusia apalagi perempuan dengan hukum-hukum sistem pergaulannya,” tukasnya.[] sumber:www.muslimahnews.com
name: Back to Muslim Identity

pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, “pertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai ‘amanah’ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa ‘kontrol seksual’ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.” kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah. “menjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,” ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019). pratma kemudian menjelaskan bahwa umat islam harus berupaya menegakkan syariat islam kaffah sebagai solusi persoalan kekerasan terhadap perempuan, “tidak kalah penting mengedukasi umat bahwa persoalan kekerasan seksual, bahkan pelecehan kehormatan perempuan tak akan terjadi jika khilafah tegak. syariat kaffah itu memiliki hukum yang amat memuliakan manusia apalagi perempuan dengan hukum-hukum sistem pergaulannya,” tukasnya.[] sumber:www.muslimahnews.com

text:
it’s me v me
.
i don’t compete with anyone but myself. i don’t compete for times.
.
i compete to see what i’m capable of. i compete to see how far i can go. i compete to see what this beautiful body is able to accomplish.
.
it’s me v me.
it’s mind v heart.
it’s mental strength v my old friends anxiety, panic and depression.
.
this time i’m going to beat them.
in this little corner of my house i find the solitude, self confidence, peace, strength, grit and rediscover my endurance.
.
ironman training isn’t fancy. it’s grit. it’s what you do when nobody else is around and looking. i love training alone. it’s meditation for me. it’s healing me to my bones these days. it’s giving me fire to fight.
.
today’s ironman training was:
60 minutes on the bike that i dragged and set up on my trainer at my kid’s soccer practice. it was an ass kicker 😈🚴🏻‍♀️
.
then day 3 of my half marathon running program. it was 2x12 mins with 4 min walk between. my incline was at 1% and i did 90 seconds at 12 min/mile - 30 seconds at 10 min/mile. repeated 6x each section.
.
i’m feeling more and more confidence in running and falling back in love with it each time. it’s sooooooooo exhilarating to be doing what i love again and feeling adrenaline and peace instead of anxiety! i’m really happy again doing this and i may be over emphasizing this all but it’s my journey back to an athlete and i’m soooooo proud because last summer i could barely move. i’m sharing this journey, this story, this training in all its nitty gritty glory because it’s accountability for me and this time it means more than ever to cross that finish line at ironman chattanooga. 🙏🏽🖤
.
i’ve done the mental and spiritual work the past 18 months and it feels pretty fucking good to be doing the physical work now. #ironmantraining #metoo #ironmanchattanooga #veganathlete

posted @withrepost • @frizzkidart today's affirmation art: all survivors are brave. all victims are brave. 💛 those who share their stories of surviving sexual violence/intimate partner violence are brave, but those who may not be able to share their stories or don't want to are also brave. no survivor/victim is cowardly and it's their choice what they want to do with their story. you may also wonder why i chose to include the word "victim." not everyone who experiences sexual violence or intimate partner violence feels like a "survivor." if we want to approach this issue in a "survivor-centric" way, then we can't impose the same strong, recovery, survival narrative on every person impacted by sexual violence/ipv. every survivor/victim is different, navigates their trauma differently, and has different perspectives on justice and healing looks like. in looking at the #metoo movement, i've seen a tendency to want to tell all stories the same way, without realizing that all survivors/victims have different intersections in their identity that a) impacts their likelihood to experience violence and b) changes the way experience justice and reconciliation with trauma. every survivor/victim is worthy of love, respect, and support. every survivor/victim is brave no matter how they choose to cope with their trauma. #art #artist #affirmation #illustration #drawing #draw #healing #heal #justice #metoo #feministart #endrapeculture #selflove #brave #torontoartist #feminist

posted @withrepost • @frizzkidart today's affirmation art: all survivors are brave. all victims are brave. 💛 those who share their stories of surviving sexual violence/intimate partner violence are brave, but those who may not be able to share their stories or do not want to are also brave. no survivor/victim is cowardly and it is their choice what they want to do with their story. you may also wonder why i chose to include the word "victim." not everyone who experiences sexual violence or intimate partner violence feels like a "survivor." if we want to approach this issue in a "survivor-centric" way, then we can not impose the same strong, recovery, survival narrative on every person impacted by sexual violence/ipv. every survivor/victim is different, navigates their trauma differently, and has different perspectives on justice and healing looks like. in looking at the #metoo movement, i have seen a tendency to want to tell all stories the same way, without realizing that all survivors/victims have different intersections in their identity that a) impacts their likelihood to experience violence and b) changes the way experience justice and reconciliation with trauma. every survivor/victim is worthy of love, respect, and support. every survivor/victim is brave no matter how they choose to cope with their trauma. #art #artist #affirmation #illustration #drawing #draw #healing #heal #justice #metoo #feministart #endrapeculture #selflove #brave #torontoartist #feminist

text:
perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks  pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.

pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya. atau gerakan #metoo yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.

pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, “pertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai ‘amanah’ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa ‘kontrol seksual’ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.” kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah. “menjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,” ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019). pratma kemudian menjelaskan bahwa umat islam harus berupaya menegakkan syariat islam kaffah sebagai solusi persoalan kekerasan terhadap perempuan, “tidak kalah penting mengedukasi umat bahwa persoalan kekerasan seksual, bahkan pelecehan kehormatan perempuan tak akan terjadi jika khilafah tegak. syariat kaffah itu memiliki hukum yang amat memuliakan manusia apalagi perempuan dengan hukum-hukum sistem pergaulannya,” tukas

text:
i promised id keep sharing my own story with you. bit by bit. so here's  some heavy thoughts...or... maybe its brightening up this dreary frigid awful cold thursday evening with  some positive thoughts. two sides of the same coin. 
i've mentioned lots of silver linings i've found through the bs that is this brca journey - all you lovely people i've connected with, a better understanding of my health...i could go on. but the other night something new and wonderful occurred to me. 
i was talking to one of my closest friends, also a survivor of sexual trauma and it occured to me... this new chest that i'm learning to love a little more everyday... my attacker has never  and will never lay eyes or vile claws on it. and somehow now i feel magically whole again, in a way i havent in over a decade. kind of amazing actually. 
what silver linings have you found  on your journey that you never thought you would see? .

text:
after nearly 12 years of very active embodied healing of myself and nearly a decade of working with mostly women on mind-body-spirit healing and empowerment (you name it...relationship issues, phobias, childhood sexual abuse and incest to serious negative entity attachments to sex trafficking prevention advocacy), something i never in a million years would have guessed happened to me on one of my many trips to #nyc last year. .

i was #violated. .

my body went into a momentary freeze, shock state. i just could not believe it. don’t think of the worst thing ever here. but it wasn’t fun, i’ll tell you that. 
bc of all the work i’ve done and continue to do on myself and bc of my extensive trainings and studies in somatic and breath based trauma healing and meditation, i actually had a choice which is rare here. but i saw i had worked my ass off for this moment: i could let the incident trigger a deep state of terror within me and bring me back to my many years of being absolutely terrified of the world (all the while appearing aggressive and seductive so you wouldn’t know it—unconsciously existing in one big trauma reenactment) or i could say, “ok god/spirit/allah, what exactly are you up to here? why this bs after all these years and why now during our #metoo time?” within an hour of #heartrhythmmeditation , i got the message: a clear download of what needed to be done. .
within a day of returning to pa, i called up @wannabe_wandering and said, “hey....i had this vision, and it goes something like this....”and she said, “that’s funny, i just had the same vision in my dream the other night.” so there you have it folks. me too berks: a time to heal (empowrong all people) was born. for more on what happened in nyc, please join me and tara for a powerful event at the miller center in march 30th. 
this is a movement that invites a shift in the conversation away from persecution and into inclusivity, healing, prevention and education. .
website is www.metooberks.com and the fb page link in my bio above! i’d be so profoundly grateful for all you local to se pa if you could help us share any of these me too posts and invite people on fb to our events! 🙏

text:
man accused of raping three children within a week was released on bail twice before being arrested!⠀
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -⠀
29-year-old raymond hernandez accused of raping three children in a week and sexually assaulting his own 13-year-old daughter has been released on bail twice from the same judge and then being arrested for the third time after a state-wide manhunt. ⠀
⠀
the man was first arrested on january 15 for raping a teenage girl and beating her friend. the judge ernest ortega released him for a $10,000 bond. he was then brought back to court and had the same judge. the judge then released him on £20,000 bail. only few days later after his second release, raymond was arrested for allegedly raping a five-year-old girl next door to his family. ⠀
⠀
neighbour gloria lucero told kob4 tv, “i’m speechless, he needs to pay, and i hope the judge puts him behind bars and keeps him there,”.⠀
⠀

text:
girls in pain get less sympathy
vidcast: https://youtu.be/_w3hodgjfp0

another goal for the #metoo movement is suggested by the latest study from yale psychologists.  as research subjects observed a video of the very same child being subjected to the classic, old fashioned medical torture, the fingerstick, but identified as either samuel or samantha, the majority of observers, both men and women, believe that the girl samantha felt less pain than the boy samuel.

this gender bias result is in synch with similar impressions of adults experiencing pain.  the result can be explained by the widespread misconception that boys are more stoic than girls, and it would take greater pain to elicit the same response in the male. 
parents of girls and significant others of women undergoing procedures need to advocate for their child or partner if they feel that the  pain management being offered is insufficient whether or not it’s due to gender bias. 
brian d earp, joshua t monrad, marianne lafrance, john a bargh, lindsey l cohen, jennifer a richeson. gender bias in pediatric pain assessment. journal of pediatric psychology, 2019; doi: 10.1093/jpepsy/jsy104

text_retweet:
reposted from @backto_muslimidentity -  perempuan butuh syariat islam, bukan ruu pks  pengamat politik dan pemerhati perempuan, pratama julia sunjandari, menilai alasan tingginya angka kekerasan seksual di indonesia yang menjadi latar belakang legalisasi rancangan undang undang (ruu) penghapusan kekerasan seksual (pks) sungguh mengada-ada.

pasalnya, menurut pratma, bukan sekadar ada umbrella act lalu persoalan kekerasan seksual selesai. perancis yang telah mengatur tentang sanksi kriminal pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja menunjukkan pejabat dunia christine lagarde yang juga mantan menkeu pransis pernah menjadi korban pelecehan seksual bersama puluhan mantan perempuan terkemuka prancis lainnya. atau gerakan #metoo yang kini mendunia menunjukkan bahwa hukum di negara-negara tersebut tidak mampu menghentikan kekerasan seksual.

pratma lalu mengungkap tiga alasan kalangan feminis ngotot ingin melegalisasi ruu pks, “pertama menyuburkan perilaku sekuler liberal. muatan srhr (sexual and reproductive healths rights) sebagai ‘amanah’ beijing platform for action (bpfa) amat kuat. frasa ‘kontrol seksual’ itu menegaskan daulat atas tubuh sehingga seorang istri berhak menolak hamil atau menolak ajakan suaminya ke tempat tidur. termasuk hak untuk meluapkan orientasi seksual pada apapun atau siapapun.” kedua, kata pratma julia, merusak keluarga terutama relasi suami istri. tak ada lagi qawwam (pemimpin) dalam rumah tangga termasuk dalam hubungan yang amat privat. ketiga, menikam syariat islam. kalangan liberal, dengan dukungan negara leluasa mengadvokasi umat untuk tidak lagi patuh pada hukum allah. “menjadi keharusan bagi kaum muslimin untuk menolak dan mencegah kemunkaran ini dengan aksi nyata,” ungkapnya kepada mnews, rabu (30/1/2019). pratma kemudian menjelaskan bahwa umat islam harus berupaya menegakkan syariat islam kaffah sebagai solusi persoalan kekerasan terhadap perempuan, “tidak kalah penting mengedukasi umat bahwa persoalan kekerasan seksual, bahkan pelecehan kehormatan perempuan tak akan terjadi jika khilafah tegak. syariat kaffah itu memiliki hukum yang amat memuliakan manusia apalagi perempuan dengan hukum-hukum sistem pergaulannya,” tukasnya.[] sumber:www.mu

text:
sisters, it is you ⁣
my healing balm. ⁣
⁣
i seek refuge in a carefully curated red tent where this anthem reminds me of my divinity and yours. rise up with me, come inside this refuge and find your own divine healing in words of truth. ⁣
⁣
'haseya'⁣
@ajeetmusic⁣
⁣
i am the river of life⁣
i am the keeper of this dream⁣
walk with me,⁣
i'll tell you a thousand stories⁣
long ago given to the earth⁣
these mountains tall⁣
they are my only walls⁣
in this temple where i bow⁣
haseya⁣
rise up my sisters, rise up⁣
we are the water, the sacred cup⁣
it's in our hands that all life grows⁣
it's in your dance, it's in your hands,⁣
it's in your love we rise above⁣
it's in your song i hear my soul⁣
so rise up my sisters, rise up⁣
let us lift each other up⁣
sing it from your heart and from your soul⁣
haseya⁣
the sun and moon they shine together⁣
she moves the waters and dances with the heavens⁣
in your eyes i see her eyes⁣
in your eyes i see the giver of this life⁣
⁣
@homeschool⁣
⁣

text:
quand je surmonte ma peur et que j’ose raconter l’agression sexuelle que j’ai subie, la première réaction des gens est de poser des questions. « t’as crié? tu t’es défendue? t’étais habillée comment? tu étais seule? tu avais bu? t’as porté plainte? t’es allée à l’hôpital?» je comprends que c’est une réaction naturelle, cette espèce de curiosité. il faut savoir que poser des questions n’apporte absolument rien à une victime, à part un sentiment de culpabilité et l’impression d’être jugée. si une personne partage une histoire traumatisante qu’elle a vécue avec vous, écoutez, soyez empathiques. gardez vos questions pour vous. ******
sometimes i face my fears, and share the story of my sexual assault with someone. their first reaction is usually to ask questions. “ did you scream? did you defend yourself? how were you dressed? were you alone? did you drink? did you report it? did you go to the hospital? ” i understand that it’s a normal reaction, this kind of curiosity. it’s important to know that asking questions doesn’t do anything for the victim except making them feel guilty and judged. if someone tells you about a traumatic experience, just listen and be empathetic. keep your questions to yourself.

#sexualtrauma #trauma #consentisnecessary #stopwiththequestions #empathetic #metoo #timesup #consent #traumatique #noustoutes #arrêtezavecvosquestions #agressionsexuelle #plusquesurvivre #survivreauviol #consentement

text:
repairing intuition.

intuition is a wonderful gift. intuition is that 6th sense; that feeling we get from our bodies telling us something is happening or is going to happen based on everything we have experienced in our lives thus far.

it’s the warning sign giving us a head’s up. sometimes we choose to ignore our intuition. 
why? 
is it denial? 
is it fear? 
is it that we don’t want to do the difficult thing in that moment and put up a boundary?

ignoring intuition stems from us learning to not trust ourselves. 
whether this was low self-esteem baked into us as children or having unhealthy relationships that made us second guess ourselves. 
it’s important to understand why we ignore our intuition first and then learn to trust our intuition and know that it’s there to guide us and that we can, and have a right, to act on it without any explanation. 
because trusting yourself to follow your intuition will not lead you astray. 
#survivortothriver #trustyourintuition #trustyourself #trustinyourself #yougotthis #lifelessons #survivorstory #dvam #trustissues #trustyourgut #relationshipadvice #recoveryquotes #metoo #metoomovement #trustyourheart

yes it's silly.  yes, sometimes i hate the way that women are portrayed on the show. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

. flashbacks
. venereal disease
. anxiety over sex
. fear of exposing the body during medical exams ————————————————————————

text: am not writing, am eating froot loops. because i’ve just spent a really hard week writing a poem about a poetess who has been my idol since 1983 but i now know bartered her underaged teenage daughters off as sexual party favours at her notorious 1970s sydney bohemian dinners. funded by taxpayers. and the men who took advantage of this? also australian writers and artists i have long admired/knew. so many people and things are dead. but not froot loops. froot loops live. am eating froot loops, and hurling books around my apartment. soon i will take the kitten for a walk, then swim in the ocean. and kudos to #katelilley for writing about what she lived through in her collection #tilt, which has just won the #victorianpremiersliteraryaward poetry prize #thelifepoetic #australianpoetry #feministwriters #metoo #dorothyhewett

text:
breach is now available online! link in bio 🙌 this is such an important film for me, because with this film i decided i not only wanted to be an actress, but a creator, a storyteller. thank you to all who were involved. 💕  breach is a short film involving power plays, a cyber attack, and taking back your power of choice. it was awarded semi-finalist in the los angeles cinefest and a rebel minded film fest

breach was the first film i wrote and produced. i created it prior to the #metoo movement taking off, and simply from my own experience. as an actress working in the business for 10 years, i've seen a lot of things. as a woman my whole life, i've seen more. breach was created based off what i was dealing with (and my female friends were also experiencing/dealing with) as an ambitious young woman in the workforce. it was created with this question in mind: what do we do now? we take back our power of choice.

text:
deepika padukone was unanimously voted as the new chairperson for the jio mami @mumbaifilmfest at the recent board meeting 👍🏼👏🏼
.
دیپیکا پادوکن به اتفاق آرا به عنوان رئیس هیئت مدیره فستيوال فيلم مومبای mami انتخاب شد 🙌👏
.
صحبت های برخی از اعضای هیئت امنا/مدیره فستيوال فيلم مومبای :
.
"ما یقین داریم که این آکادمی تحت رهبری دیپیکا پادوکن، قدرت بیشتری در خدمت رسانی به جامعه ی سینما خواهد یافت.
علاوه بر این، مدیریت وی قطعا باعث خواهد شد که فستيوال، حمایت مالی لازم را دریافت کند."
.
"دیپیکا در دوره ی حضور خود به عنوان یکی از اعضای هیئت مدیره فستيوال فيلم مومبای طی چند سال گذشته، نقشی اساسی در تصمیم گیری های مهم داشته است.
.
✔ در رابطه با جنبش #metoo این دیپیکا بود که قاطعانه درخواست کرد که فیلم هایی که ساخته ی افرادی هستند که به صورت جدی به آزار جنسی متهم شده اند، از اکران و رقابت در این فستيوال کنار گذاشته شوند.
صحبت های او بر روی تمامی اعضا تاثیر گذاشت و در نهایت فستيوال هم در این جهت اقدام کرد."
.
* کبیر خان، ویشال باردواج، کاران جوهر، زویا اختر، فرهان اختر، ویکرام آدیتیا متوانه، سیدارت روی کاپور، انوپاما چوپرا، کران رائو، ... از دیگر اعضای هیئت امنا فستيوال فيلم مومبای mami هستند.
.

tweet_full:
deepika padukone was uimously voted as the new chairperson for the jio mami @mumbaifilmfest at the recent board meeting 👍🏼👏🏼
.
دیپیکا پادوکن به اتفاق آرا به عنوان رئیس هیئت مدیره فستيوال فيلم مومبای mami انتخاب شد 🙌👏
.
صحبت های برخی از اعضای هیئت امنا/مدیره فستيوال فيلم مومبای :
.
"ما یقین داریم که این آکادمی تحت رهبری دیپیکا پادوکن، قدرت بیشتری در خدمت رسانی به جامعه ی سینما خواهد یافت.
علاوه بر این، مدیریت وی قطعا باعث خواهد شد که فستيوال، حمایت مالی لازم را دریافت کند."
.
"دیپیکا در دوره ی حضور خود به عنوان یکی از اعضای هیئت مدیره فستيوال فيلم مومبای طی چند سال گذشته، نقشی اساسی در تصمیم گیری های مهم داشته است.
.
✔ در رابطه با جنبش #metoo این دیپیکا بود که قاطعانه درخواست کرد که فیلم هایی که ساخته ی افرادی هستند که به صورت جدی به آزار جنسی متهم شده اند، از اکران و رقابت در این فستيوال کنار گذاشته شوند.
صحبت های او بر روی تمامی اعضا تاثیر گذاشت و در نهایت فستيوال هم در این جهت اقدام کرد."
.
* کبیر خان، ویشال باردواج، کاران جوهر، زویا اختر، فرهان اختر، ویکرام آدیتیا متوانه، سیدارت روی کاپور، انوپاما چوپرا، کران رائو، ... از دیگر اعضای هیئت امنا فستيوال فيلم مومبای mami هستند.
.

text:
rp @thesavemovement 💛 @sheffieldanimalsave 💛 another victim of the dairy industry.

we spotted this mother heading into the slaughterhouse this morning, her throat was already slit and her blood had been drained.

we will likely never know the reason why she was killed before being taken to the slaughterhouse or what happened during her final moments alive.

we do however know what her time alive will have been like.

dairy cows live a life of constant torment.

they are pregnant for 3/4 of the year and have every calf removed immediately after being born.

she spent the majority of her life knowing that her unborn child would be taken from her.

now her lifeless body lays in the back of this truck, broken and spent, she will soon end up incinerated.
.
.

text:
reviewing book 13th for 2019🌸
.
so i will be posting daily from now onwards and have been planning to take february on a more creative path. 
plus yaay it's my birthday month.
.
it's official, stupid by sid baliga is a blend of a corporate #metoo story and a true love story. 
the story starts with astitha joining the corporate world and as she falls head over heels for her manager mr. joby joseph she is taken aback to her college memories and romance. the flashbacks of her and her college romantic sumanth tells us that sumanth was deeply in love with astitha however due to bad health and no career goals astitha decided to dump sumanth. astitha's manager mr. joby is mesmerized by astitha and confesses her that he truly liked her and their relationship takes a step ahead from the corporate relationship they already shared. just as the relationship of joby and astitha takes a start, sumanth is destined to meet astitha and come back in her life. the story makes us believe that joby and astitha may end up together as their love was already noticeable by the other corporate colleagues  and family. however not until astitha goes missing and sumanth turns restless and joby seems too formal. that's when the #metoo  story is revealed and  sumanth's true love is appreciated.
the story is pretty relatable with the real life incidences however the story needed to be defined a little more precisely. 
the title of the book is cool and the cover too is pretty. 
rating: 🌟🌟🌟/5

text:
this is agnes titus. agnes has been a leader in the women’s rights movement across the pacific for decades. after helping to secure peace in bougainville, following the civil war in the 1990s, she threw her time, energy and passion into reducing violence against women in bougainville. 
agnes is from the nazareth centre for rehabilitation, a leading organisation in bougainville challenging the norms that allow violence against women to exist. we’re so proud to partner with her and the nazareth team!

text:
01.31.2019
•
it’s said that time can heal wounds, and that really is true. however there are some wounds that you live with you’re entire life... that’s emotional wounds. people tend to focus on their physical health more then their mental health which is where things can get tricky because your emotions can be so strong they cause physical ailments. •
the emotional wounds i am about to talk about are not for everyone but i just needed to share how you can overcome some serious emotional wounds... when i was fifteen years old, nine years ago today actually, i was date raped. it took me years to be able to not blame myself for what happened and it took me years to be so open and honest about it. 
however, when the man, after six years and who was going to be your husband says “did he really f*** you up that bad” during the last argument of your relationship i realized how much emotional abuse i’ve been letting roll over my shoulder because i cared more about others then i did for myself.
•
today you have a woman who has been used and abused. a woman who doesn’t have time for bs. a woman who knows what she deserves in life and isn’t going to allow anything else. •
when i made this page i focused on selling makeup. now, i use this page to share my journey of life and health through my essential oil journey, my natural and cruelty free beauty care, and now a big part of my emotional health history. i hope that none of you have the same past as i do... but if you do just know i am here to talk if you need it. •
things can get ugly, but the beauty will radiate from within. ✨🌱💗
•
#littledidyouknow #metoo #emotionalabuse #butasyoubreakme #selflovetoselfstrength #selflovegoesalongggway

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
☀️8 years ago today i made one of the biggest and best decisions of my life. my only "regret" was not going with a better lawyer at the time, at the time it was more important to be divorced asap. i had to make a lot of sacrifices but i am so much better off now than i could have ever been.👩‍👦‍👦
🗣 if you are stuck in a crappy relationship, get out- if you dont think you can, you can and people will help you! if your partner doesnt support you, lift you up, make you strive to be a better person, make you feel warm and safe when they hug you, let you be the real you, then leave! life will suck for a bit, but then it will better than ever before. 💖
#8yearsoflivingmybestlife #8yearsofhappiness #liveforyourself #domesticviolence #domesticviolenceawareness #saveyourself #youcandoit #metoo #survivor

text:
i never understood what true love was until i fell at the feet of jesus. i came from a home that had very dysfunctional ways of showing love that was passed down generation after generation. we call those generational curses in the body of christ. -
-
i had a hard time forgiving people, forgiving my parents, forgiving people who betrayed me, until i realized jesus forgave me even at my worst and not only did he forgive me, he picked me up and loved me despite it all. talk about unconditional love right? -
-
if you’re struggling to see what true love is, how you should be loved, how you should be cherished, look to jesus. we might not all come from the loveliest homes and loveliest role models, but we do have the best one available 24/7 and his name is jesus christ, the son of god. ❤️

text:
according to the times, cambridge analytica bought the data from aleksandr kogan, a russian-american academic. kogan, who told facebook he was conducting academic research, built a facebook personality quiz app called "thisisyourdigitalife." when users downloaded the app, it scraped all of their available facebook data, including their friends, their likes and where they lived.

more than a quarter-million facebook users downloaded the app, which also exploited a facebook vulnerability that allowed it to to collect most of the same data from the friends of those who downloaded it. by prying into the friends lists of those who made the download, kogan was able to get data from more than 50 million people.

throughout 2015 and into 2016, the cruz campaign paid cambridge analytica almost $6 million for data that the campaign used for what it called "psychographic targeting," which supposedly allowed the campaign to tailor its message to specific voters in places like iowa and new hampshire, where single voters can make a big difference. using data from the firm, the campaign built profiles of potential voters, prioritizing those who fit in categories such as "stoic traditionalist" and "true believer". in december 2015, the same month the guardian revealed cambridge analytica and kogan's data harvesting practices, cruz campaign spokesman rick tyler called the company a "market leader and the best in the field." despite tyler's claim that the cruz campaign stopped using the firm's data in early 2016, it kept paying cambridge analytica until june of that year, a month after cruz suspended his campaign. after cruz dropped out of the race, the firm began working with trump, supporting him through november's general election against hillary clinton.

stephen young
dallas observer

text:
she was one of the first voices to start speaking publicly, as a rape survivor in india. gang-raped as a teenager in mumbai and indignant at the deafening silence on the issue, #sohailaabdulali wrote an article for an indian women’s magazine questioning the way we perceive rape. 30 years later, the story went viral post the 2012 delhi rape & global outcry.

in 'what we talk about when we talk about rape' (@penguinindia), sohaila writes not just as a survivor, but also as a counsellor and activist. her book explores not only what we think about rape & what we say, but also what we don't say. it encourages us to ask the hard questions, look deeper and introspect further. enjoy our selection of quotes from the book, & share with your friends.

#mumbai folks, join us for an evening of stimulating conversation between sohaila and our very own @dizibot at @g5afoundation on 4th february (monday)! rsvp: link in bio.
.

.

text:
結論から言うと。まずは国会でやれ。海外じゃやってるとこもある！

#スッキリ でこんなアンケートやると聞いて。怒り通り越して脱力。

私の職場にも保育園、小学校休みで実家や夫の都合で子ども見てられないからって。時々子ども連れて来る人いるけどな。

そこら辺走り回って車椅子にぶつかりそうになったり。大きな声で泣いたり叫んだり。扱い間違えると危ないもの触ったり。

子ども連れてないスタッフも気を使うし。ハラハラするんだよ！子どもだって始終「お行儀よくしなさい」って言われてかわいそうだし。

そもそも国会からして。妊娠しただけで一部の国民から
こんな時に妊娠しなくても😒とか。ちゃんと仕事してるのか？😒みたいな言われ方するよな。妊娠した女性議員が。
妊娠させた方はスルーでさ！

結論。今期の国会の議決場でテストしてみろ！議決場で実際に「自分達が保育士さん」の保育園してみたら子連れ出勤推奨が如何に愚策か分かる。

#子どものいる生活 #子育て支援 #子連れ出勤可能 より #保育園 作って #保育士の給料あげてください 
これまで通り女性に押し付けておしまい！なら #feminism #フェミニズム と #metoo も追加で。
hashtags: #スッキリ, #子どものいる生活, #子育て支援, #子連れ出勤可能, #保育園, #保育士の給料あげてください, #feminism, #フェミニズム, #Metoo

text:
huge news for the team at @wayfarerla i am so excited for them!  fourteen months ago i entrusted my #metoo story to a group of strangers in los angeles.

i was extremely thankful to get the trauma out of my system that was my personal reward. to take my power back and feel cleansed of the experience.

i am thankful i listened to a dear friend and made the right choice to share my story to this team.

congratulations to the team at wayfarer entertainment i am so thankful for your vision and courage.

more impact, stories and opportunity. this is great news! #beingkarenalston #wayfarerentertainment #dreambigger #makenosmallplans #socialimpact #justinbaldoni #storytelling #impactfunds #metoo

text:
you said that you loved me
tell me why does it feel 
like a thousand tiny cuts 
cascading across my skin 
why does it feel like love is just a weapon
you wield to keep me locked in

all this time later 
still feels like yesterday 
pieces of me 
caught in the fray
i have nothing left to say 
heart weighted down by hate 
peeling back the layers of my rage
broken and betrayed 
but i refuse to stay that way
light awaits 
i cannot say how long this wound
will remain 
can only love me back to me again ————————————————— poem by marley monroe/ 📸photographer: marley monroe// recovery comes in baby steps. sorrow, in waves. all i know is i will not stop until all of me emanates light once again, and i will not let what right now feels like a trauma that defines me, take over my heart. 💖🦋 #photography #poetsofinstagram #poetry #photographer #lyrics #metoo #poetrycommunity #singersongwriter #singersofinstagram #sunsets

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

do you love it when you can purchase something and help those in need at the same time? i know i do! ✋

this nail wrap is our current founders design for fadv (fight against domestic violence) and it is called happiness. each time this nail wrap is purchased a portion of the proceeds goes to a local domestic violence shelter to help those victims with crucial resources. my family was once a ricepient of such resources and i can assure you, each dollar counts. 💜 
so when you are shopping this valentine's day for the perfect gift, outfit, mani, etc please consider this nail wrap. not only will it make anyone's nails pretty, it will also help a family become safe. what better gift could you give? ~
~
~

text:
wow. this was the one movie i wanted to watch here. 
i haven’t shared much of my #metoo experiences except with a select few. 
i don’t know if i wanted to see this for a sense of closure or to know i’m not alone or just to feel something since i close off my emotions so much....
but to know what a corruption of power looks like in any industry and to understand why and how people don’t speak up or even just to see what things are said and done to people....and it’s not always by the offender. the rumors and the blame...
anyway. 
well done. thank you for sharing your stories and making this documentary. #sundancefilmfestival #untouchable

text:
people say a lot of things...
.
.
people say a lot of things.  they tell you who they are, what they’re about, what they stand for...what they believe.  they tell you their pasts, they tell you their futures, they even tell you their present.  and i believe they believe everything they say. .
.
i think it’s important to be a great listener but i’m starting to think it’s even more important to watch people. the actions and behaviors of people speaks volumes... sometimes more than their words.  but the staff and volunteers of the @eastlosangeleswomenscenter does both.  they speak up against the social injustices held against women and they show up and provide comprehensive care for survivors, like free counseling, case-working, shelter, advocacy, and a number of other services.  these amazing people deserve to be recognized and honored for their incredible and amazing service. .
.
i’m proud to say #dcastmusic made a small donation to elawc from some of the profits made from the “i’m a beautiful mess” t-shirts.  i’m honored to partner with them for this upcoming album and pledge to give them half the profits from the music.  cuz people do say a lot of things and they do like to tell who they are and what they believe.  but the heroes at elawc really don’t have to tell anybody anything...they’re too busy letting their actions speak for themselves. 👸🏽✊🏾💜
.
.

text:
this photo popped up on my facebook as being posted 1 year ago today, timely given i arrived back in istanbul yesterday.

the caption was:
"
watching those around me return to europe for christmas and new year i began to miss this summer season in australia. being so far away it was a difficult decision to make, as i picked apart the pros and cons of forking out for a flight home and how i felt i was quitting or somehow failing for returning.
i reminded myself i don't have anything to prove and that summer is a wonderful time of year in australia. now i am essentially holidaying in my home country: reading loads of books, connecting with nature and seeing the people i love 🏖📚
"

last year was a massive year of transformation, primarily spiritually and around self love, but on top of that i was also suffering pretty severe ptsd from a sexual assult while travelling.

i am so grateful to my support network, i deeply love you and cannot express what you mean to me. my moving to canberra was an accidental and clearly necessary part of my healing and i miss and think about you all a lot.

@kiah.s @heymilicuda_ @lauralilliann @strippermonologues @mallory_berryman @qqquiet @sinafever @deeeids 
now here i am back in my favourite city, 🕌☕istanbul🇹🇷❄ , just over a year later. i am not a failure, my life is so incredibly wild and adventurous and i am so proud of myself for being so open to change and growth.
